ww.motor1.com/news/100186/mercedes-generation-eq-concept-reveal/|title=Mercedes Generation EQ concept electrifies Paris with 402 hp|work=Motor1.com|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en}}</ref> The final production version was revealed in Sweden on September 4, 2018,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thedrive.com/tech/23339/on-site-in-stockholm-for-the-all-new-mercedes-benz-eqc-400-reveal|title=On Site in Stockholm for the All-New Mercedes-Benz EQC 400 Reveal|last=Condon|first=Josh|work=The Drive|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-US}}</ref> and publicly debuted at the [[2018 Paris Motor Show]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autoexpress.co.uk/mercedes/eq/102353/new-electric-mercedes-eqc-suv-revealed-with-280-mile-range|title=New electric Mercedes EQC SUV revealed with 280-mile range|work=Auto Express|access-date=2018-09-07|language=en}}</ref>{{update after|2020|2|26}}<!-- did this car make it to production?  any reviews?  there are crash test results; but nothing sourced that indicates the car is in production now in Feb 2020 -->\n\n== Design ==\n<gallery mode=\"nolines\" widths=\"250\">\nFile:Mercedes, Paris Motor Show 2018, Paris (1Y7A1362).jpg|EQC400 4MATIC rear\nFile:Mercedes-Benz EQC (04).jpg|Interior\n</gallery>\n\nThe EQC is based on the [[Mercedes-Benz GLC-Class|GLC]] and shares the same [[wheelbase]] dimensions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/new-mercedes-benz-eqc-all-electric-suv-revealed|title=New Mercedes-Benz EQC: all-electric SUV revealed {{!}} Autocar|website=www.autocar.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501164146/https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/new-mercedes-benz-eqc-all-electric-suv-revealed|archive-date=2019-05-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> It is a five-seater vehicle and has a trunk capacity of {{Convert|500|litres|ft3}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autoexpress.co.uk/mercedes/eq/102353/mercedes-eqc-electric-suv-spied-in-production-form|title=New electric Mercedes EQC SUV revealed with 280-mile range|work=Auto Express|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe EQC400 4MATIC is powered by 2 asynchronous [[electric motor]]s, fitted on the front and rear axles, and produces {{convert|300|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/mercedes-benz-eqc-electric-suv/|title=Mercedes Challenges Tesla With an All-Electric SUV|work=WIRED|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-US}}</ref> It has an electronically limited top speed of {{convert|180|kph|mph|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.slashgear.com/2020-mercedes-benz-eqc-electric-suv-revealed-range-specifications-tech-04544357/|title=2020 Mercedes-Benz EQC revealed: EV range, power & all the tech|date=2018-09-04|work=SlashGear|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThe 80 kWh [[battery pack]] has a modular design and consists of 384 [[lithium-ion battery|lithium-ion cells]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/michaeltaylor/2018/09/04/better-late-than-never-as-eqc-leads-mercedes-benz-ev-assault/|title=Better Late Than Never As EQC Leads Mercedes-Benz EV Assault|last=Taylor|first=Michael|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en}}</ref> It can be charged from 10 to 80 percent in 40 minutes, via a DC [[fast charger]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/09/04/mercedes-benz-unveils-the-eqc-to-kick-off-12-billion-electric-offensive/|title=Mercedes-Benz unveils the EQC to kick off $12 billion electric offensive|work=TechCrunch|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nSteering wheel paddle shifters allow for the selection of varying levels of [[regenerative brake|brake energy regeneration]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://driving.ca/mercedes-benz/auto-news/news/first-look-2020-mercedes-benz-eqc|title=First Look: 2020 Mercedes-Benz EQC|date=2018-09-04|work=Driving|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Equipment ==\nStandard equipment includes 19-inch alloy wheels, [[collision avoidance system|automatic collision avoidance]], and two 10.25-inch interior displays for the instrument cluster and infotainment system.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.slashgear.com/2020-mercedes-eqc-electric-suv-five-things-to-know-04544362/|title=5 things to know about the 2020 Mercedes EQC electric SUV|date=2018-09-04|work=SlashGear|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-US}}</ref> All models feature the Mercedes-Benz User Experience (MBUX) system, which features a [[voice user interface|voice-controlled]] [[personal digital assistant|smart-assistant]] that can be activated by saying \"Hey Mercedes\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cars.com/articles/look-out-tesla-heres-the-eqc-the-mercedes-benz-of-electric-suvs-1420702793297/|title=Look Out Tesla: Here's the EQC, the 'Mercedes-Benz of Electric SUVs'|website=cars.com|access-date=2018-09-05}}</ref> It can display charging information and energy consumption figures.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.caradvice.com.au/682061/2020-mercedes-benz-eqc-revealed/|title=2020 Mercedes-Benz EQC revealed: 300kW EV debuts in Stockholm {{!}} CarAdvice|work=CarAdvice.com|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-GB}}</ref> The [[navigation system]] can also suggest routes that include [[charging station]]s depending on the remaining charge of the battery,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.auto123.com/en/news/mercedes-benz-eqc-electric-crossover-world-premiere/65070/|title=Mercedes-Benz EQC all-electric crossover makes world debut {{!}} Car News {{!}} Auto123|work=auto123.com|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en-CA}}</ref> as well as simple destination entry using [[what3words]].{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Models ==\nThe specifications include:{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Model\n!Years\n!Power\n!Torque\n!0\u2013100&nbsp;km/h (0-62&nbsp;mph)\n!Top speed\n!Range(WLTP)\n!Range(EPA)\n|-\n|EQC400 <br> 4MATIC\n|2019\u2013\n|{{convert|300|kW|hp|0|abbr=on|disp=br()}}\n|{{convert|760|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on|disp=br()}}\n|5.1 s\n|{{convert|180|kph|mph|0|abbr=on|disp=br()}}\n|{{convert|417|km|mi|0|abbr=on|disp=br()}}\n|{{convert|354|km|mi|0|abbr=on|disp=br()}}\n|}\n\n== Safety ==\nThe 2019 EQC received five stars overall in its [[Euro NCAP]] test.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euroncap.com/en/results/mercedes-benz/eqc/38095|title=Official Mercedes-Benz EQ C 2019 safety rating|website=www.euroncap.com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-06}}</ref>\n{{Euro NCAP\n|year=2019\n|overall_stars=5\n|description=Mercedes-Benz EQC 400 4MATIC\n|adult_points=36.6\n|adult_percent=96\n|child_points=44.1\n|child_percent=90\n|pedestrian_points=36.2\n|pedestrian_percent=75\n|safety_points=9.9\n|safety_percent=75\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat|Mercedes-Benz EQC}}\n* [https://www.mercedes-benz.com/en/mercedes-benz/vehicles/eqc-2019/ Official site]\n\n{{Mercedes-Benz timeline 1990\u20132019}}\n{{Mercedes-Benz timeline 2020 to date}}\n\n[[Category:Mercedes-Benz vehicles|EQC]]\n[[Category:Battery electric cars currently in production]]\n[[Category:All-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2018]]\n[[Category:Crossover sport utility vehicles]]\n[[Category:Electric sport utility vehicles]]\n", "name_user": "TKOIII", "label": "safe", "comment": "cat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercedes-Benz_EQC"}
