crets''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/brigitte-nielsen-adi-shankars-gods-and-secrets-1202495808/|title=sitemap|work=twcc.com}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n* 1988 ''[[Every Body Tells a Story]]''\n* 1992 ''[[I'm the One... Nobody Else]]''\n* 2008 ''Brigitte Nielsen'' (re-release of ''[[I'm the One... Nobody Else]]'' and ''[[Every Body Tells a Story]]'')\n\n===Singles===\n* \"Body Next to Body\" \u2013 [[Falco (musician)|Falco]] meets Brigitte Nielsen; 1987; (No. 6 [[Austria]], No. 22 Germany, No. 1 [[Oricon|Japan]])\n* \"Every Body Tells a Story\"; 1987; (No. 38 Italy; No. 15 Germany)\n* \"Maybe\"; 1988\n* \"Siento\"; 1988 (South America only)\n* \"It's a Strange Love\"; 1988\n* \"Rockin' Like a Radio\"; 1990\n* \"My Girl (My Guy)\"; 1991\n* \"How Could You Let Me Go?\"; 1992\n* \"Work That Body\"; 1993\n* \"No More Turning Back\" (as Gitta); 2000; released by [[Jive Records|Jive]]; (No. 1 Spain, No. 1 [[Eurodance]] [[chart]]; No. 64 Netherlands, No. 54 UK)\n* \"Everybody's Turning Back\" (as Gitta vs. [[Rozalla]])\n* \"Tic Toc\" (as Gitta); 2001; released by [[Blanco y Negro Music|Blanco y Negro]]\n* \"You're No Lady\" (as Gitta with [[Ru Paul]]); 2002; released by Do It Yourself; (No. 1 Spain)\n* \"Misery\" (as Gitte Nielsen with [[Spleen United]]); 2012\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Brigitte Nielsen}}\n* {{official site|http://www.brigittenielsen.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|557}}\n* {{discogs artist|106998}}\n\n{{Ich Bin Ein Star \u2013 Holt Mich Hier Raus! (series 6)}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nielsen, Brigitte}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish actresses]]\n[[Category:Danish female models]]\n[[Category:Danish female singers]]\n[[Category:Danish film actresses]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Denmark]]\n[[Category:Ich bin ein Star \u2013 Holt mich hier raus! winners]]\n[[Category:La Ferme C\u00e9l\u00e9brit\u00e9s participants]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from R\u00f8dovre]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Birgit Nilsson}}\n{{short description|Danish actress, model and singer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Brigitte Nielsen\n| image        = Brigitte_Nielsen.jpg\n| caption      = Nielsen at [[London Fashion Week]] in 2010\n| birth_name   = Gitte Nielsen\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1963|07|15|df=yes}}  \n| birth_place  = [[R\u00f8dovre]], Denmark\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| occupation   = Actress, model, singer\n| years_active = 1984-present\n| spouse       = {{marriage|Kasper Winding|1983|1984|end=}}<br>{{marriage|[[Sylvester Stallone]]|1985|1987|end=}}<br>{{marriage|[[Sebastian Copeland]]|1990|1992|end=}}<br>{{marriage|Raoul Meyer|1993|2005|end=}}<br>{{marriage|Mattia Dess\u00ec|2006}}\n| partner      = [[Mark Gastineau]] (1988-1990)<br>[[Flavor Flav]] (2005)\n| children     = 5\n| website      = http://www.brigittenielsen.com/\n}}\n\n'''Brigitte Nielsen''' ({{IPA-da|p\u0281i\u02c8kit\u0259 \u02c8ne\u031dlsn\u0329}}; born '''Gitte Nielsen'''; 15 July 1963) is a Danish actress, model, singer and reality television personality. She began her career modeling for Greg Gorman and [[Helmut Newton]]. She subsequently acted in the 1985 films ''[[Red Sonja (film)|Red Sonja]]'' and ''[[Rocky IV]]'', later returning to Rocky series in ''[[Creed II]]'' (2018). She is also known for her marriage to [[Sylvester Stallone]], with whom she starred in the 1986 film ''[[Cobra (1986 film)|Cobra]]''. She played a villain in ''[[Beverly Hills Cop II]]'' (1987) and starred as the Black Witch in the 1990s Italian film series ''[[Fantaghir\u00f2 series|Fantaghiro]].'' She later built a career starring in B-movies, hosting TV shows, and appearing on reality shows.\n\n==Early life==\nBrigitte Nielsen was born Gitte Nielsen in [[R\u00f8dovre]], a suburb of [[Copenhagen]], Denmark. She is the daughter of Hanne, a librarian, and Svend Nielsen, an engineer,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.filmreference.com/film/14/Brigitte-Nielsen.html|title= Brigitte Nielsen Biography}}</ref> and the ex-sister-in-law of ''[[Drive (2011 film)|Drive]]'' director [[Nicolas Winding Refn]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Modeling===\nStanding 1.85 m (6'1\"), at the beginning of the 1980s, Nielsen did some modeling work, and was photographed by [[Greg Gorman]]<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://danskmagazine.com/covergirls/brigitte-nielsen-by-greg-gorman/#comments |title=Brigitte Nielsen by Greg Gorman |publisher=Danskmagazine.com |date=2010-02-10 |accessdate=2011-06-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708231113/http://danskmagazine.com/covergirls/brigitte-nielsen-by-greg-gorman/#comments |archivedate=2011-07-08 |df= }}</ref> and [[Helmut Newton]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://danskmagazine.com/fashiontheory/brigitte-nielsen-by-helmut-newton/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100211145753/http://danskmagazine.com/fashiontheory/brigitte-nielsen-by-helmut-newton/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2010-02-11 |title=Brigitte Nielsen by Helmut Newton |publisher=Danskmagazine.com |date=2010-02-08 |accessdate=2011-06-18 }}</ref> Nielsen posed for ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine multiple times, garnering the cover in December 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dtmagazine.com/cmopg1924/pb1287.html |title=Playboy magazine December 1987 Gore Vidal Brigitte Nielsen Sex Stars |publisher=Dtmagazine.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref><ref>[https://www.amazon.com/PLAYBOY-DECEMBER-Brigitte-Nielsen-pictorial/dp/B0012G1J7 <!-- accessdate=June 25, 2011 -->]{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> In the late 1980s, [[Marvel Comics]] approached Nielsen to pose for photographs dressed as the comic book character [[She-Hulk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shulkie.com/node/26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071006132631/http://shulkie.com/node/26 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2007-10-06 |title=Brigitte Nielsen as She-Hulk &#124; She-Hulk Fan Site |publisher=Shulkie.com |date=2007-05-12 |accessdate=2011-10-26 }}</ref> Nielsen's exploits were well-covered in the entertainment media in the 1980s, and the world press started referring to her as an \"Amazon\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-3826261.html|title=Brigitte Nielsen attacks image as film Amazon|date=May 17, 1987|publisher=Highbeam.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102133751/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-3826261.html|archive-date=November 2, 2012|url-status=dead|accessdate=June 18, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.com.mt/news.asp?newsitemid=35404|title=What's good for the Danish goose, but not for the Maltese gander?|date=July 9, 2006|publisher=Independent.com.mt|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120218042843/http://www.independent.com.mt/news.asp?newsitemid=35404|archive-date=February 18, 2012|url-status=dead|accessdate=June 18, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/strange-love-vol-63-no-11/|title=Strange Love|date=March 21, 2005|work=People|accessdate=February 25, 2019}}</ref> because of her tall stature.\n\n===Acting===\nIn 1985, Nielsen began her acting career in the fantasy film ''[[Red Sonja (film)|Red Sonja]]'' alongside [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]]. That same year, she married [[Sylvester Stallone]]; the couple acted in two films together (''[[Rocky IV]]'' and ''[[Cobra (1986 film)|Cobra]]'') before divorcing in 1987.\n\nIn 1987, Nielsen played Karla Fry in the film ''[[Beverly Hills Cop II]]'' (1987), alongside [[Eddie Murphy]]. Subsequently, she starred in ''[[976-Evil II]]'', ''[[The Double 0 Kid]]'' (1992), ''[[Chained Heat II]]'' (1993), ''[[Galaxis]]'' (1995), and ''[[Snowboard Academy]]'' (1996). She starred as the villainess of the Italian TV fantasy film ''[[Fantaghir\u00f2 2]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1992/agosto/28/Fantaghiro_attenti_strega_Brigitte_co_0_92082810044.shtml|title=Fantaghiro' 2, attenti a strega Brigitte|author=Calcagno Paolo|publisher=Archiviostorico.corriere.it|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref> and [[Fantaghir\u00f2 series|its sequels]] (1992\u20131996); her character was supposed to be killed off in the first of these films, but was then brought back due to popular demand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.film.it/news/televisione/dettaglio/art/che-natale-sarebbe-senza-fantaghir-La-saga-fantasy-torna-su-mediaset-44593/|title=Che Natale sarebbe senza Fantaghir\u00f2? La saga fantasy torna su Mediaset|website=www.film.it|language=it|access-date=2019-05-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Nielsen voice acted for the Danish animated comedy film ''[[Ronal the Barbarian]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.imdb.it/title/tt1629374/ |title=RONAL BARBAREN (2011) IMDB profile |publisher=Imdb.it |date=2009-05-01 |accessdate=2011-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721102519/http://www.imdb.it/title/tt1629374/ |archive-date=2011-07-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2012, she played in the horror movie ''[[Eldorado (2012 film)|Eldorado]]''. In 2013, she has featured in the short art film ''The Key'' alongside [[Ray Stevenson (actor)|Ray Stevenson]]. In 2014, she starred in the science-fiction film ''Exodus'',<ref name=\"giantfreakinrobot.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.giantfreakinrobot.com/scifi/danish-scifi-project-exodus-unique-approach-visual-effects.html|title=Danish Sci-Fi Project Exodus Uses Unique Approach To Visual Effects|work=Giant Freakin Robot|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref> in the TV series ''[[Raising Hope]]'', and in the action film ''[[Mercenaries (2014 film)|Mercenaries]]''. In 2017, she joined the cast of TV series ''Adi Shankar's Gods and Secrets''. In 2018, she reprised her role of Ludmilla Drago from ''Rocky IV'' in ''[[Creed II]]''.\n\n===Music and writing===\nNielsen started a music career in 1987. She released her debut album ''[[Every Body Tells a Story]]'' in that year and recorded a duet with Austrian pop star [[Falco (musician)|Falco]], [[Giorgio Moroder]]'s penned \"[[Body Next to Body]]\" which went to No. 22 in Germany and No. 6 in Austria.<ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://www.austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Falco+meets+Brigitte+Nielsen&titel=Body+Next+To+Body&cat=s |title=''Body Next to Body'' \u2013 Austrian Chart Archive |publisher=Austriancharts.at |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref> She released a follow-up album, ''[[I'm the One... Nobody Else]]'', in 1991.\n\nNielsen released a few songs under the pseudonym \"Gitta\" because producers wanted to see if she could succeed as a singer without her name on the cover. The first song \"No More Turning Back\" peaked at No. 54 on the British Single Charts,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/9404/gitta/ |title=GITTA Official Charts |publisher=officialcharts.com |date= |accessdate=2015-08-06}}</ref> No. 63 on the Dutch Single Charts<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swisscharts.com/song/Gitta/No-More-Turning-Back!!-171993 |title=GITTA - NO MORE TURNING BACK!! |publisher=Hitparade.ch |date= |accessdate=2015-08-06}}</ref> and even reached the Top 10 in Spain.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-g8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA67&dq=gitta+%22no+more+turning+back%22+charts+spain#v=onepage&q=gitta%20%22no%20more%20turning%20back%22%20charts%20spain |title=Hits of the world (cont.) |publisher=Billboard Magazine |date= 2000-07-15|accessdate=2015-08-06}}</ref> Other tracks recorded as Gitta were 2001's \"Tic Toc\" and 2002's \"You're No Lady\", a collaboration with [[Ru Paul]].\n\nNielsen appeared in [[Michael Jackson]]'s \"[[Liberian Girl]]\" music video in 1989 and in metal band [[Korn]]'s music video for the single \"[[Make Me Bad]]\" in 2000. In 2008, German record label [[Edel Music]] re-released her 1991 album ''I'm the One... Nobody Else'' and the 1987 ''Every Body Tells a Story'' under the title ''Brigitte Nielsen''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.edel.de/Aktuell.77.0.html?&L=0&artist=9577&cHash=a53e08f56c |title=Edel Music Germany) |publisher=Edel.de |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718233019/http://www.edel.de/Aktuell.77.0.html?&L=0&artist=9577&cHash=a53e08f56c |archive-date=2011-07-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2012, she performed (as Gitte Nielsen) on the song \"Misery\" with [[Spleen United]], from the album ''[[School of Euphoria]]''.\n\nIn 2009, she published her first autobiography in Scandinavia titled \"''Gitte Nielsen \u2013 Du har kun \u00e9t liv \u2013 s\u00e5dan fandt jeg tilbage til mig selv''\" (\"You only have one life \u2013 this is how I found myself again\").<ref>{{cite web|author=Af admin |url=http://www.kulturplakaten.dk/du-har-kun-et-liv-selvbiografi-af-gitte-nielsen/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719125535/http://www.kulturplakaten.dk/du-har-kun-et-liv-selvbiografi-af-gitte-nielsen/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-07-19 |title=Article published by ''Kulturplakaten on 15 September 2009 |publisher=Kulturplakaten.dk |date=1999-02-22 |accessdate=2011-06-18 }}</ref> The book reached the Top5 of Denmark's bestseller list<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brigittenielsen.com/index.php?section=news&next=17 |title=Brigitte Nielsen official website |publisher=Brigittenielsen.com |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref> and was released in the United Kingdom under the title ''You Only Get One Life'' in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tesco.com/books/product.aspx?R=9781843583424&bci=4294314408|title=You only get one life \u2013 Tesco Books |publisher=Tesco.com |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref>\n\n===Television===\nNielsen has worked for Italian television, hosting shows such as: ''Festival'' (1987), the 1992 edition of the [[Sanremo Music Festival]], ''Retromarsh!'' (1996\u20131997), and ''..la sai l'ultima?'' (1999). In 1997, she hosted a talk show series ''Gittes venner'' for a Danish TV network and some TV shows for [[RTSI]], the [[Italian language]] Swiss television network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.faktalink.dk/titelliste/talk/talktalk |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029110635/http://www.faktalink.dk/titelliste/talk/talktalk |url-status=dead |archive-date=29 October 2014 |title=Talkshows i Danmark |publisher=Faktalink.dk |accessdate=29 October 2014 }}</ref> She guest starred for an episode of the German TV series ''[[Stuttgart Homicide]]'', aired by [[ZDF]] on 28 March 2011,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zdf.de/ZDFmediathek/beitrag/video/1132974/Brigitte-Nielsen-bei-SOKO-Stuttgart#/beitrag/video/1132974/Brigitte-Nielsen-bei-SOKO-Stuttgart |title=Video Interview by www.zdf.de |publisher=Zdf.de |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610044653/http://www.zdf.de/ZDFmediathek/beitrag/video/1132974/Brigitte-Nielsen-bei-SOKO-Stuttgart#/beitrag/video/1132974/Brigitte-Nielsen-bei-SOKO-Stuttgart |archivedate=2011-06-10 |df= }}</ref> guest-hosted the British chat show ''[[Loose Women]]'' on 7 December 2010. In April 2011, she attended the British variety/talent show ''[[Sing If You Can]]'', which aired on ITV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/pressreleases/programmepressreleases/singifyoucan/default.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110404115209/http://www.itv.com/presscentre/pressreleases/programmepressreleases/singifyoucan/default.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-04-04 |title=Press Releases \u2013 SING IF YOU CAN / |publisher=Itv.com |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18 }}</ref>\n\nNielsen appeared on the first season of the Italian production of ''[[The Mole (TV series)|The Mole]]'' (2004) and on the third season of the VH1 reality show ''[[The Surreal Life]]'' (2004). Nielsen also appeared with Flav on VH1's Big in '04 Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/vh1-big-in-04/|title=VH1 Big In '04|publisher=Cbsnews.com|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref> In 2006, she guest-starred on Flav's other reality show, ''[[Flavor of Love]]''. In 2003, Nielsen appeared in the Danish ''Big Brother VIP''. In January 2005, she was a contestant in Britain's ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 2005 (UK)|Celebrity Big Brother]]'', along with her former mother-in-law, [[Jackie Stallone]], coming third in the final public vote. In 2006, she appeared in another reality TV series, VH1's ''[[The Surreal Life: Fame Games]]''. In 2007, she starred in a new British mockumentary ''Killing Brigitte Nielsen'', which aired on [[Sky Travel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a43123/sky-travel-to-air-killing-brigitte-nielsen.html|title=Sky Travel to air 'Killing Brigitte Nielsen'|work=Digital Spy|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref> She also appeared in the first season of ''[[Celebrity Rehab with Dr. Drew]]'', which chronicled her struggle to overcome her [[alcoholism]] at the Pasadena Recovery Center in [[Pasadena, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/inside-vh1s-controversial-show-celebrity-rehab-vol-69-no-5/|title=Inside Vh1's Controversial Show Celebrity Rehab|work=People|accessdate=February 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2008, Nielsen revealed on German television that she would \"renew\" her body by having six plastic surgeries, which would cost \u20ac66,000 altogether. She was filmed during those surgeries by [[RTL Television|RTL]] and she had her own television show ''Aus alt mach neu \u2013 Brigitte Nielsen in der Promi-Beauty-Klinik''. The same show was broadcast twice in Italy: at first under the title ''Celebrity Makeover: Brigitte Nielsen'' on [[SKY Italia]] in 2008 and secondly in 2009 on [[Italia 1]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguida.com/2009/07/24/brigitte-nielsen-e-la-chirurgia-plastica-celebrity-bisturi-parte-su-italia-1-il-10-agosto |title=Article appeared in TVGuida.com on 24 July 2009 |publisher=Tvguida.com |date=2011-02-21 |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref> In 2009, Nielsen appeared as a panel speaker to a new group of addicts at the Pasadena Recovery Center, anticipating the two-year mark of her sobriety that coming July. Her appearance was aired in the third-season episode \"Triggers\", which aired in February 2010.<ref name=Triggers>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/video/celebrity-rehab-3/full-episodes/triggers/1631736/playlist.jhtml|title=''Celebrity Rehab with Dr. Drew'' Episode 3.6 (\"Triggers\") VH1; 11 February 2010|work=vh1.com|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Nielsen appeared as one of the celebrity contestants of [[TF1]] reality show ''[[La Ferme C\u00e9l\u00e9brit\u00e9s]]'', the French version of the TV series ''[[The Farm (TV series)|The Farm]]''. She was eliminated after one week, mainly due to her lack of fluency in French and subsequent difficulties to interact with the other contestants.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://la-ferme-celebrites.programme-tv.net/la-ferme-celebrites-2009/candidats/266-brigitte-nielsen/ |title=La ferme c\u00e9l\u00e9brit\u00e9s : Brigitte Nielsen |publisher=La-ferme-celebrites.programme-tv.net |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716143420/http://la-ferme-celebrites.programme-tv.net/la-ferme-celebrites-2009/candidats/266-brigitte-nielsen/ |archive-date=2011-07-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"Brigitte Nielsen interview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/actualite-people-medias/brigitte-nielsen-je-me-sens-coupable-07-02-2010-806895.php |title=Brigitte Nielsen : \" Je me sens coupable \" |publisher=Leparisien.fr |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref> Nielsen was one of the celebrity contestants of 2010's ''Let's Dance'', the German version of ''[[Dancing with the Stars]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtl.de/cms/unterhaltung/tv-programm/show/kandidaten-lets-dance.html |title=LET'S DANCE \u2013 Rtl Official Site |publisher=Rtl.de |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref> That same year, she also took part of ''Celebrity [[Come Dine With Me]]'' in Denmark (''Til middag hos... ''),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billedbladet.dk/Kendte/Nyheder/2010/7/Gitte%20Nielsen%20til%20middag%20hos.aspx |title=Billed-Bladet \u2013 Til middag hos Gitte Nielsen |publisher=Billedbladet.dk |date=2010-07-05 |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref> and in Germany (''Das Perfekte Promi Dinner'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vox.de/kochen/das-perfekte-promi-dinner/portrait/id/404/tn_id/1852/Brigitte__Nielsen |title=Das perfekte Promi Dinner \u2013 Brigitte Nielsen |publisher=VOX.de |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref>\n\nFrom 13 January 2012 Nielsen was one of the celebrity contestants and winner of ''[[Ich bin ein Star \u2013 Holt mich hier raus!]]'', the German version of ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]'', broadcast by [[RTL Television]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtl.de/cms/sendungen/ich-bin-ein-star/dschungelcamp-kandidaten/brigitte-nielsen.html |title=Dschungelcamp 2012: Brigitte Nielsen |publisher=RTL.de |date= |accessdate=2012-01-06}}</ref> On 28 January 2012 she won the show as the \"Jungle Queen\". ''[[Bildzeitung]]'' revealed on 30 January 2012 that Nielsen had received the most calls from TV viewers throughout the entire show, ranking No.1 with 30 \u2013 50% of all call-ins.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bild.de/dschungelcamp/2012/dschungelcamp/die-geheimen-abstimmungs-protokolle-ergebnisse-22349832.bild.html|title=Dschungelcamp: Die geheimen Abstimmungs-Protokolle|date=|publisher=Bild.de}}</ref> Nielsen was paid 150.000 Euro (approx. $163,000) for participating in the show, more than any other celebrity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/thema/dschungelcamp/dschungelcamp_2012/brigitte-nielsen-erhaelt-die-hoechste-gage-im-rtl-camp-id6232340.html |title=Brigitte Nielsen erh\u00e4lt die h\u00f6chste Gage im RTL-Camp |publisher=DerWesten.de |date=2011-01-11 |accessdate=2015-08-06}}</ref> In October 2012, Nielsen was featured in the Danish version of [[Maestro (TV series)|Maestro]] broadcast on [[DR1]] in which celebrities competed for the chance to conduct a classical orchestra. In September 2013, she joined the cast of the German TV show ''Promi-Hochzeitsplanern'' (''Celebrity Wedding planners'') for [[Sat.1]]. The following year, she joined the panel of the German TV show ''Promi Shopping Queen'' for [[VOX (German TV channel)|VOX]].\n\nFrom June 2015, she has hosted her own talk show \"Gitte Talks\" on the Danish TV Channel [[Kanal 4]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kanal4.dk/gitte-nielsen-f%C3%A5r-eget-talkshow-p%C3%A5-kanal-4|title=Gitte Nielsen f\u00e5r eget talkshow - Gitte Nielsen f\u00e5r eget talkshow - Kanal4|work=kanal4.dk}}</ref> From August 2016, she has also presented the [[dating show]] \"Wirt sucht Liebe\" (\"Is Looking for Love\") for the German TV channel [[RTL II]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtl2.de/sendung/wirt-sucht-liebe/folge/folge-1-87|title=Folge 1|website=www.rtl2.de}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBesides her native Danish, Nielsen is fluent in English, German and Italian,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.intriguemanagement.co.uk/index.php?id=8 |title=Intrigue Management \u2013 The Celebrity Management & Talent Agency |publisher=Intriguemanagement.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref> and has some understanding of French.<ref name=\"Brigitte Nielsen interview\"/>\n\n===Family and relationships===\n[[File:Sylvester Stallone Brigitte Nielsen.jpg|thumb|Brigitte Nielsen with [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Ronald Reagan|Ronald]] and [[Nancy Reagan]] at the [[White House]], 1985]]\n\nNielsen has been married five times and has four sons and one daughter. Her first husband was Kasper Winding, to whom she was married in 1983\u201384, and they have one son, Julian Winding (he was largely raised by his father, with little contact between them).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://go.tv2.dk/articlefornoejelse/id-19848990.html|title=Julian Winding er stolt af mor!|publisher=Go.tv2.dk|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nNielsen married actor [[Sylvester Stallone]] on December 15, 1985 at the [[Beverly Hills, California]] home of producer [[Irwin Winkler]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,290699,00.html|title=A Rocky Marriage|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=December 12, 1997|accessdate=2011-12-24}}</ref> Stallone and Nielsen's marriage lasted 19 months, with their divorce finalized in July 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/cover-story-gitte-finds-her-mark-vol-29-no-13/|date=April 4, 1988|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|title=Gitte Finds Her Mark|first=Joanne |last=Kaufman|first2= Jorgen |last2=Salomonsen|first3= Alan|last3= Richman|accessdate=February 25, 2019}}</ref> Their marriage and divorce were both highly publicised by the tabloid press.<ref name=\"autogenerated27\">Susan Zannos, ''Male Fitness Stars of TV and the Movies: Featuring Profiles of Sylvester Stallone, John Travolta, Bruce Willis and Wesley Snipes'', Mitchell Lane Publishers, 2000, page 27</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1755&dat=19870723&id=vqMcAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RXAEAAAAIBAJ&pg=7140,3399728 \"Stallone divorce stops Tabloid presses\"], ''[[Sarasota Herald-Tribune]]'' \u2013 23 July 1987.</ref><ref name=\"nytimes1997\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/10/movies/stallone-seeks-a-serious-turn-for-the-better.html|title=Stallone Seeks a Serious Turn for the Better \u2013 Page 3 \u2013 ''The New York Times''|date=1997-08-10|accessdate=2011-10-26|publisher=Nytimes.com}}</ref> They had no children. Her second child, Killian Marcus Gastineau (born in 1989), was fathered by her ex-fianc\u00e9 [[Mark Gastineau]].\n\nBetween 1990 and 1992, she was married to director and photographer [[Sebastian Copeland]] ([[Orlando Bloom]]'s cousin). They had no children. Nielsen has two sons with fourth husband Raoul Meyer, Douglas Aaron (born in April 1993) and Raoul, Jr. (born in May 1995).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.klatsch-tratsch.de/2014/08/11/brigitte-nielsen-zeigt-sich-hier-erstmals-mit-ihren-vier-sohnen/213060|title=Brigitte Nielsen zeigt sich hier erstmals mit ihren vier S\u00f6hnen - klatsch-tratsch.de|work=klatsch-tratsch.de|accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nDuring a 2012 interview on the German reality TV show ''Ich bin ein Star \u2013 Holt mich hier raus!'', she confessed to having had a one-night stand with [[Sean Penn]] in [[Cannes]] back in the early 1990s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtl.de/cms/sendungen/ich-bin-ein-star/dschungelcamp-2012-brigitte-nielsen-ich-hatte-einen-one-night-stand-mit-sean-penn-1e47d-a382-93-1001277.html |title=Dschungelcamp 2012: Brigitte Nielsen: \"Ich hatte einen One-Night-Stand mit Sean Penn |publisher=RTL.de |date= |accessdate=2012-01-24}}</ref> In 2005, she had a highly publicized relationship with rapper [[Flavor Flav]].\n\nHer current husband, Mattia Dess\u00ec (born on October 22, 1978), lived with her in Italy as shown on ''[[Strange Love]]'', which was filmed prior to their marriage. The couple got married in Malta on July 8, 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20060708/local/the-great-dane-marries-in-malta.48361 |title=The Great Dane marries in Malta |publisher=Times of Malta |date=2006-07-08 |accessdate=2018-06-03}}</ref> {{as of|2010}}, they live in [[Palm Springs]], USA.<ref name=Rochlin>{{Citation| last = Rochlin| first = Margy| author-link = | author2-link = | title = Addicted to Rehab| newspaper = [[TV Guide]]| pages = 34\u201335| date = 1 February 2010| url = }}</ref> On 28 May 2018, Brigitte Nielsen announced that she was pregnant with her fifth child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BjSyjHzHrj9/ |title=Brigitte Nielsen on Instagram |date= |accessdate=May 31, 2018}}</ref> In June, she gave birth to a daughter, Frida,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/brigitte-nielsen-welcomes-fifth-child-at-54-daughter-frida/|title=Baby at 54! Brigitte Nielsen Welcomes Fifth Child, Daughter Frida: 'We Are Overjoyed'|work=People|date=June 23, 2018}}</ref> at the age of 54 (her first girl).\n\n===Alcohol problems===\nOn July 9, 2007, Nielsen checked herself into the Cri-Help [[Drug rehabilitation|rehabilitation]] facility in [[North Hollywood]] following what some reports claim was a family [[Intervention (counseling)|intervention]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news.nsf/article/nielsen%20in%20rehab_1037977 |title=Sylvester Stallone &#124; Nielsen In Rehab |publisher=Contactmusic |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref> Her manager, Steven Tempone, confirmed on 19 July 2007 that she had checked into a rehabilitation center and said, \"All I know is it's something she did of her own free will and we're proud of her and wish her very well... When she gets out we'll have a big birthday party, and [[Coca-Cola]] only.\"<ref>[http://www.voanews.com/english/2007-07-20-voa40.cfm <!-- |accessdate=July 24, 2007 --> ]{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> As of 22 July 2007, Nielsen was out of rehabilitation to attend the [[Comedy Central Roast of Flavor Flav|Comedy Central roast of Flavor Flav]]. She remarked that she felt \"like a new-born person&nbsp;... I made a choice about a new life. It's not been easy but it was definitely time.\" While the date that Nielsen checked into rehabilitation was reported, she \"had been in treatment for a few weeks.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Rodriguez |first=Brenda |url=https://people.com/celebrity/brigitte-nielsen-i-feel-reborn-after-rehab/ |title=Brigitte Nielsen: I Feel Reborn After Rehab \u2013 Brigitte Nielsen|work=People|date=July 23, 2007|accessdate=February 25, 2019}}</ref> On January 10, 2008, [[VH1]] began airing the reality TV series ''[[Celebrity Rehab]]''. Nielsen appeared on the show for alcoholism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/dyn/celebrity_rehab_with_dr_drew/series.jhtml |title=Celebrity Rehab 5 &#124; Show Cast, Episodes, Guides, Trailers, Web Exclusives, Previews |publisher=VH1.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref> In a January 2010, ''[[TV Guide]]'' story on her success with sobriety, ''Celebrity Rehab'' producer John Irwin stated, \"She's sober, and she quit smoking.\"<ref name=\"Rochlin\" />\n\n===Plastic surgery===\nIn mid-2008, Nielsen starred in the reality show ''Aus alt mach neu'', broadcast by the German TV-station RTL. The theme of the show was Nielsen's attempt to look \"as young as her husband\" by undergoing plastic surgery. The show was aired in Italy as well, on [[Sky Italia|SKY]] Italia during December 2008<ref name=\"tvblog.it\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvblog.it/post/11773/celebrity-spot-makeover-brigitte-nielsen-su-sky-vivo |title=Article appeared on TvBlog.it on 10 December 2009 |publisher=Tvblog.it |date= |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref> and the following summer on Italia 1.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvblog.it/post/15003/italia1-elisabetta-gregoraci-conduce-celebrity-bisturi-con-le-operazioni-estetiche-di-brigitte-nielsen |title=Article appeared on TvBlog.it on 23 July 2009 |publisher=Tvblog.it |date=2011-04-20 |accessdate=2011-06-18}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1985 \n|''[[Red Sonja (film)|Red Sonja]]''\n|[[Red Sonja]]\n|\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Rocky IV]]''\n|Ludmilla Drago\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Cobra (1986 film)|Cobra]]''\n|Ingrid Knudsen\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[Beverly Hills Cop II]]''\n|Karla Fry\n|\n|-\n|1988\n|''[[Bye Bye Baby (film)|Bye Bye Baby]]''\n|Lisa\n|\n|-\n|1988\n|''[[Domino (1988 film)|Domino]]''\n|Domino\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''Murder by Moonlight''\n|Maggie Bartok\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[976-Evil II]]''\n|Agnes\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''{{sortname|The|Double 0 Kid}}''\n|Rhonda\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''Mission of Justice''\n|Dr. Rachel K. Larkin\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Fantaghir\u00f2 2]]''\n|Black Witch (Black Queen)\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Fantaghir\u00f2 3]]''\n|Black Witch\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Chained Heat II]]''\n|Magda Kassar\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Fantaghir\u00f2 4]]''\n|Black Witch\n|\n|-\