17/tv/news/brigitte-nielsen-adi-shankars-gods-and-secrets-1202495808/|title=sitemap|work=twcc.com}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n* 1988 ''[[Every Body Tells a Story]]''\n* 1992 ''[[I'm the One... Nobody Else]]''\n* 2008 ''Brigitte Nielsen'' (re-release of ''[[I'm the One... Nobody Else]]'' and ''[[Every Body Tells a Story]]'')\n\n===Singles===\n* \"Body Next to Body\" \u2013 [[Falco (musician)|Falco]] meets Brigitte Nielsen; 1987; (No. 6 [[Austria]], No. 22 Germany, No. 1 [[Oricon|Japan]])\n* \"Every Body Tells a Story\"; 1987; (No. 38 Italy; No. 15 Germany)\n* \"Maybe\"; 1988\n* \"Siento\"; 1988 (South America only)\n* \"It's a Strange Love\"; 1988\n* \"Rockin' Like a Radio\"; 1990\n* \"My Girl (My Guy)\"; 1991\n* \"How Could You Let Me Go?\"; 1992\n* \"Work That Body\"; 1993\n* \"No More Turning Back\" (as Gitta); 2000; released by [[Jive Records|Jive]]; (No. 1 Spain, No. 1 [[Eurodance]] [[chart]]; No. 64 Netherlands, No. 54 UK)\n* \"Everybody's Turning Back\" (as Gitta vs. [[Rozalla]])\n* \"Tic Toc\" (as Gitta); 2001; released by [[Blanco y Negro Music|Blanco y Negro]]\n* \"You're No Lady\" (as Gitta with [[Ru Paul]]); 2002; released by Do It Yourself; (No. 1 Spain)\n* \"Misery\" (as Gitte Nielsen with [[Spleen United]]); 2012\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Brigitte Nielsen}}\n* {{official site|http://www.brigittenielsen.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|557}}\n* {{discogs artist|106998}}\n\n{{Ich Bin Ein Star \u2013 Holt Mich Hier Raus! (series 6)}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nielsen, Brigitte}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish actresses]]\n[[Category:Danish female models]]\n[[Category:Danish female singers]]\n[[Category:Danish film actresses]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Denmark]]\n[[Category:Ich bin ein Star \u2013 Holt mich hier raus! winners]]\n[[Category:La Ferme C\u00e9l\u00e9brit\u00e9s participants]]\