hp|0|abbr=on}}, {{convert|362|Nm|0|abbr=on}}\n|}\n\nBlueEFFICIENCY package is standard on all versions of V-Class featuring the 7G-TRONIC PLUS automatic transmission and is optionally available for all variants with 6-speed manual transmission.\n\nBlue Efficiency package is available for Vito with OM 651 engine and rear-wheel drive, and standard for all Vito models with automatic transmission and a car registration.\n\nOverboost is available for vehicles with 7G-TRONIC PLUS transmission and AGILITY SELECT, with transmission mode set to \"Comfort\" (C), \"Sport\" (S), or \"Manual\" (M).\n\n===Transmissions===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\"\n|+Diesel engines\n!Model!!Years!!Types\n|-\n|V 200 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS with DIRECT SELECT lever and DIRECT SELECT shift paddles)\n|-\n|V 220 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS with DIRECT SELECT lever and DIRECT SELECT shift paddles)\n|-\n|V 250 BlueTEC||2014-||7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS with DIRECT SELECT lever and DIRECT SELECT shift paddles)\n|-\n|Vito 109 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual\n|-\n|Vito 110 CDI||2020-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual\n|-\n|Vito 111 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual\n|-\n|Vito 114 CDI||2014-2020||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS)\n|-\n|Vito 114 CDI||2020-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 9-speed ''[[9G-Tronic]]'' [[automatic transmission|automatic]]\n|-\n|Vito 116 CDI||2014-2020||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS)\n|-\n|Vito 116 CDI||2020-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 9-speed automatic (9G-Tronic)\n|-\n|Vito 119 BlueTEC||2014-||7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS)\n|-\n||Vito 119 CDI||2020-||9-speed automatic (9G-Tronic)\n|-\n||Vito 124 CDI||2020-||9-speed automatic (9G-Tronic)\n|-\n|eVito Tourer||2021-||Single speed with fixed ratio\n|}\n\nV-Class with 7G-TRONIC PLUS transmission includes optional AGILITY SELECT system with 4 transmission modes (\"ECO\" (E), \"Comfort\" (C), \"Sport\" (S) and \"Manual\" (M)).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www5.mercedes-benz.com/en/vehicles/passenger-cars/v-class/ Mercedes-Benz V-Class]\n* [http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/_639.flash.html?csref=mbuk_viano_url_061211 Mercedes-Benz Viano (UK)]\n* [http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/van/home/new_vans/the-new-vito.html Mercedes-Benz Vito (UK)]\n*[http://www.mbvans.com/sprinter/commercial-vans/metris-cargo-van MB Vans - Metris Cargo Van]\n\n{{Mercedes-Benz timeline 1990\u20132019}}\n{{Mercedes-Benz timeline 2020 to date}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[Category:Mercedes-Benz buses|Vito]]\n[[Category:Vans]]\n[[Category:Minibuses]]\n[[Category:Vehicles introduced in 1996]]\n[[Category:1990s cars]]\n[[Category:2000s cars]]\n[[Category:2010s cars]]\n[[Category:2020s cars]]\n[[Category:Front-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Rear-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Cars powered by VR engines]]\n[[Category:Mercedes-Benz trucks|Vito]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|A light commercial van}}\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = Mercedes-Benz V Class/Vito\n| image = Mercedes-Benz V 250 d Exclusive AMG Line Lang (V 447) \u2013 Frontansicht, 29. Juni 2016, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg\n| aka = {{unbulleted list|Mercedes-Benz Vito (Van)|Mercedes-Benz Viano (MPV)|Mercedes-Benz V-Class (MPV)|Mercedes-Benz Marco Polo (Campervan)|Mercedes-Benz Metris (North American Models)|Mercedes-Benz EQV (electric)|Mercedes-Benz eVito Tourer (electric)}}\n| manufacturer = [[Daimler-Benz]] (1996\u20131998)<br>[[DaimlerChrysler]] (1998\u20132007)<br>[[Daimler AG]] (2007\u2013present)\n| production = 1996\u2013present\n| assembly = Spain: [[Vitoria-Gasteiz]] (Mercedes-Benz Espana, S.A.)\n| predecessor = [[Mercedes-Benz MB100]]<br>[[Mercedes-Benz R-Class]]\n| class = [[Light commercial vehicle]] ([[M-segment|M]])\n| body_style = [[Van]]<br/>[[Minibus]]\n| layout = \n| engine = 2.0 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM654 engine|OM654]] [[Inline-four engine|I4]] CDI Diesel<br /> 2.1 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM651]] [[Inline-four engine|I4]] CDI Diesel<br />3.0 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM642 engine|OM642]] [[V6 engine|V6]] CDI Diesel\n| transmission = 5-speed [[Automatic transmission|automatic]]<br />6-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]<br /> 7-speed automatic\n| related = \n}}\n\nThe '''Mercedes-Benz Vito''' is a [[light commercial vehicle|light commercial]] [[van]] ([[M-segment|M]]) produced by [[Mercedes-Benz]]. It is available as a standard [[panel van]] for cargo (called Vito), or with passenger accommodations substituted for part or all of the load area (called '''V-Class''' or '''Viano''').\n\nThe V-Class/Viano is a [[Minivan|large MPV]]. The first generation went on sale in 1996. The second generation was introduced in 2004, and the vehicle received the new Viano name. In 2010, the vehicle was facelifted with revised front and rear bumpers and lights. The interior was also improved with upgraded materials and new technology. The third generation was launched in 2014 and returned to being called V-Class.\n\nThe Viano is available in both rear- and four-wheel-drive configurations and comes in three lengths, two wheelbases and a choice of four petrol and diesel engines (as well as two specialist tuned models) coupled to either a six-speed manual or five-speed [[Tiptronic|TouchShift]] automatic transmission.\n__TOC__\n{{clear}}\n\n=={{Anchor|W638}}First generation (W638; 1996\u20132003)==\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz V 220 CDI Trend (W 638) \u2013 Frontansicht, 12. August 2013, Velbert.jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-Benz V-Klasse (front)]]\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz V 220 CDI Trend (W 638) \u2013 Heckansicht, 12. August 2013, Velbert.jpg|thumb|Mercedes-Benz V-Klasse (rear)]]\n\nThe first generation [[Mercedes-Benz]] Vito was produced between 1996 and 2003. It is powered either by a diesel engine with up to {{convert|120|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} or a gasoline engine with up to {{convert|140|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} and a [[front-wheel drive]] drivetrain. The range of gasoline engines consists of two old units from Mercedes (113 and 114) and a [[Volkswagen]] 2.8 VR6 engine, designated as the M104.900. When it comes to diesel engines, old 2.3 with and without turbo and also modern CDI 2.2 engines are available.\n\nThis body design was also sold as the V-Klasse in more luxurious and expensive version (V-Klasse was replaced with the Viano-name for the second generation of Vito). The Viano also included less van like features to the Vito such as only two seats in the front and a larger and more spacious seating capacity. At first many Vito drivers who wanted a spacious, small van opted for the Vito microbus which was extremely similar to the Viano, apart from its more van like and less luxurious features. The Viano was however a good, more car like option to the Vito microbus.  It was designed by Michael Mauer from 1989 to 1991, when the final design was chosen and patented in February 1993.<ref>[http://press.porsche.com/more_about/executives/pag/mauer.php \"Mercedes-Benz Vito\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202081500/http://press.porsche.com/more_about/executives/pag/mauer.php |date=2 February 2017 }}. ''Press Porsche''. Retrieved 2 June 2014.</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n=={{Anchor|W639}}Second generation (W639; 2003\u20132014)==\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = W639\n| image = Mercedes vito 2 v sst.jpg\n| aka = Mercedes-Benz Viano<br />Mercedes-Benz Valente (Australia)<br />Mercedes-Benz V-Class (Japan)\n| assembly = {{ubl |Spain: [[Vitoria, Spain|Vitoria-Gasteiz]] (Mercedes-Benz Espana, S.A.) |Spain: [[Alcobendas]] ([[Complete knock down|CKD]]) |Mexico: [[Santiago Tianguistenco]] |China: [[Fuzhou|F\u00fazh\u014du]] ([[Fujian Daimler Automotive|Fujian Daimler]])}}\n| production = 2003\u20132014 (Spain)<br />2008\u2013present (Mexico)<br />2010\u20132015 (China)\n| body_style = 4-door [[van]]<br/>4-door [[minibus]]\n| engine = 2.1 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM646 engine#OM646 DE22 LA|OM646 980]] [[Straight-4|L4]] Turbo Diesel (China)<br>2.1 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM646 engine|OM646 DE22 LA R]] [[Straight-4|L4]] Diesel<br>2.1 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM651 DE22]] [[Straight-4|L4]] Diesel<br>3.0 L [[Mercedes-Benz OM642 engine|OM642]] [[V6]] Diesel<br>2.5 L [[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine#E25|M272 924]] [[V6]] Diesel (China)<br>3.0 L [[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine#E30|M272 939]] [[V6]] Diesel (China)<br>3.2 L [[Mercedes-Benz M112 engine|M112 E32]] [[V6]] Petrol (2010\u2013)<br>3.5 L [[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine|M272 E35]] [[V6]] Petrol<br>3.7 L [[Mercedes-Benz M112 engine|M112 E37]] [[V6]] Petrol<br>4.3 L Brabus [[V6]] Petrol<br>6.0 L [[Mercedes-Benz M119 engine|M119]] Brabus [[V8 engine|V8]] Twin-Turbo Petrol\n| transmission = 6-speed [[Manual transmission|Manual]]<br>5-speed [[Automatic transmission|TouchShift (Automatic)]]\n| layout = [[Front engine, rear-wheel-drive layout|FR Layout]]<br>[[Front-engine, four-wheel-drive layout|F4 Layout]]\n| wheelbase = {{convert|3200|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (SWB) <br> {{convert|3430|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (LWB)\n| length = {{convert|4748|-|5223|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| width = {{convert|1906|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| height = {{convert|1875|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight = {{convert|2040|-|2135|kg|abbr=on}}\n}}\n[[File:Mercedes W639 rear 20080127.jpg|thumb|The rear of the Second generation Vito|alt=|left]]\nSix or seven seats come as standard in most markets. The Viano can be turned into an eight-seat people carrier by fitting two three-seater benches in the rear. All rear seats slide in 1-inch (2.5&nbsp;cm) increments, recline and can be turned to face one other. They can also be folded down or removed completely to increase the load capacity. A rear folding table is standard in six- and seven-seat layouts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/overview/design.0003.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Overview - Design |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100724202502/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/overview/design.0003.html |archivedate=24 July 2010}}</ref> The rear seats cannot be folded into the floor like on some rivals.\n\nWith all the seats removed the Viano Extra-Long can accommodate up to {{convert|4610|L|cuft}} of cargo<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/overview/design.0004.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Overview - Design |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100623052221/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/overview/design.0004.html |archivedate=23 June 2010 }}</ref> with a payload of {{convert|930|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/technicaldata.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Viano - Technical data |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100619112003/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/technicaldata.html |archivedate=19 June 2010}}</ref> It can tow a {{convert|2500|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} braked trailer and a {{convert|750|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} unbraked trailer. An adjustable self-levelling rear suspension is included on higher specification models.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/equipment_accessories/standard_optional_equipment.0005.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Lines and equipment - Standard equipment |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100514214057/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/equipment_accessories/standard_optional_equipment.0005.html |archivedate=14 May 2010 }}</ref>\n\nRear-wheel drive allows the Viano to have a smaller turning circle than front-wheel drive rivals; Compact and Long models have a turning circle of {{convert|11.8|m|ft|abbr=on}} whereas the Extra-Long model turns in {{convert|12.5|m|ft|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whatcar.com/Review/EditionCompare?newOrUsed=New&makeId=13298&modelId=14658&editionId=14674&makeId1=13298&modelId1=14658&editionId1=14675&makeId2=13298&modelId2=14658&editionId2=14676 |title=Mercedes-Benz Viano MPV 3.0 CDI Ambiente SWB 5dr - Car Comparison - What Car? |publisher=Whatcar.com |accessdate=26 September 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727001453/http://www.whatcar.com/Review/EditionCompare?newOrUsed=New&makeId=13298&modelId=14658&editionId=14674&makeId1=13298&modelId1=14658&editionId1=14675&makeId2=13298&modelId2=14658&editionId2=14676 |archivedate=27 July 2011  }}</ref>\n\nJapan passenger models were sold as the V-Class, as the V 350. Early models included V 350 Trend (RHD), V 350 Ambiente (RHD), V 350 Ambiente long (RHD).<ref>[http://www.mercedes-benz.jp/news/release/2011/20110121.pdf \u30e1\u30eb\u30bb\u30c7\u30b9\u30fb\u30d9\u30f3\u30c4\u65b0\u578bV \u30af\u30e9\u30b9\u3092\u767a\u58f2]</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Mercedes-Benz released the Valente model in Australia to sit beneath the Viano as the entry-level passenger van.\n\n===Initial release===\n\n====Vito====\n{{Multiple image | align = left | direction = vertical | width = 220\n| image1 = Beijing Emergency Medical Centre MB Vito.jpg\n| image2 = A 999 RTW \u4eacMX9638@2.jpg\n| caption2 = Mercedes-Benz Vito Ambulance in Beijing, China\n}}\nThe Vito was launched in China in April 2010. Engine choices consisted of the 2.1 litre [[Mercedes-Benz OM646 engine|OM646]] turbo diesel four-cylinder, the 2.5 litre [[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine|M272]] diesel V6 and the 3 litre diesel V6 which also uses the M272 name. A 6 speed manual gearbox is standard for four cylinder diesel variants while V6 diesel variants are equipped to a 5 speed automatic gearbox. Trims levels are available known as the 2.1T Diesel Elite. 2.1T Diesel Service, 2.5L Elite, 2.5L Service, 3.0L Service and 3.0L Business. Pricing ranges from 316,000 yuan to 389,000 yuan (46,000 to 55,830 USD - March 2020 exchange rate).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://car.autohome.com.cn/config/spec/7347.html#pvareaid=3454541|title=2010 Mercedes Benz Vito 2.1 litre diesel amd 2.5 litre V6 diesel specs (Chinese market)}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://car.autohome.com.cn/config/spec/15505.html#pvareaid=3454541|title=2013 Mercedes Benz Vito 3 litre V6 diesel specs (Chinese market)}}</ref> For actual car badging, the 2.1 litre Diesel models were known as the 115 CDI, the 119 for 2.5 litre V6 models and the 122 for 3 litre V6 models. The W639 Vito was then succeeded by the W447 in 2016 although most Vitos of the W639 variant are still in use for the Chinese market as of 2020 as ambulance vans in Beijing. \n \nThe second generation [[Mercedes-Benz]] Vito design that is more streamlined than its predecessor, powered by a new range of engines, and a [[rear-wheel drive]](RWD) drivetrain.\n\nThe angle of the [[windshield]] and [[pillar (car)|A-pillar]] is closer to [[Horizontal plane|horizontal]]; the [[dashboard]] is bigger and the [[hood (vehicle)|bonnet]] (hood) smaller. The new Vito is available in three different lengths and four diesel engine versions: the 109 CDI, 111 CDI, 115 CDI (all powered by a 4-cylinder 2.2-litre engine) and the 120 CDI (featuring the 3.0-litre V6 unit). The model numerics relate to their engine power output: currently the 109 has {{convert|95|PS|kW hp|abbr=on}}, the 111 has {{convert|116|PS|kW hp|abbr=on}}, the 115 has {{convert|150|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}}, and the 120 has {{convert|204|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}}. Blue-efficiency technology is optional. The vehicles have a new 6-speed manual gearbox gear ratios designed for fuel economy. The second generation Vitos are [[European emission standards|Euro]] 3 compliant (additionally Euro 4 compliant as of November 2006) and exempt from the [[London low emission zone|Low Emission Zone]] in London, which requires commercial vehicles (vans) to reach at least Euro 3 standard from October 2010.\n\n====Vito London Taxi====\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz VITO London taxicab.jpg|thumb|Vito London Taxi|alt=|left]]\nIn August 2008, a variant of the Vito was approved by the [[Public Carriage Office]] for use as a licensed London '[[Hackney carriage|black cab]]'.<ref>{{cite web|title=Public Carriage Office notice at Transport for London |url=http://www.glaciervehicles.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/13-08-mercedes-benz-vito-taxi.pdf |accessdate=8 July 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714113453/http://www.glaciervehicles.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/13-08-mercedes-benz-vito-taxi.pdf |archivedate=14 July 2014  }}</ref> The Vito taxicab includes electric sliding doors, electric steps and seating for six people. The Vito's rear-wheel steering enables it to meet the PCO's strict [[Conditions of Fitness]] requirements including a {{convert|25|ft|m|abbr=on}} turning circle and wheelchair accessibility.<ref>[http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard/article-23500360-details/Hail,+the+new+London+cab/article.do Hail, the new London cab], ''London Evening Standard'', 26 June 2008  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080819223034/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard/article-23500360-details/Hail%2C%2Bthe%2Bnew%2BLondon%2Bcab/article.do |date=19 August 2008 }}</ref> The vehicle, a variation of the 'Traveliner' model, is built by Penso in Coventry. The rear wheel steer system is licensed from one80, and it is distributed through Eco City Vehicles subsidiary KPM-UK Taxis.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/transport/2791681/Mercedes-Benz-to-launch-eco-friendly-London-black-cab.html Mercedes-Benz to launch eco-friendly London black cab], ''The Daily Telegraph'', 17 June 2008</ref>\n\nThe new Taxi does not perform the famous U-turn in the same way as the TX and Metro models {{clarify |date=July 2017 |reason= which cars are referred to here?}}, instead it incorporates an electrically operated rear wheel system, activated by a button adjacent to the steering wheel. This turns the rear wheels in the opposite direction to the front wheels, thus allowing the Taxi to perform the same tight turning circle as the TX and Metro models. This system is only possible when the vehicle is traveling at less than {{convert|5|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}, and if the vehicle goes over this speed while the LSM is active, it is deactivated, and the wheels straighten up.\n\nIt is longer and wider than the TX models, but traveling through tight spaces is aided by the electric folding wing mirrors, which as of 2009 are standard.\n\n====Viano Marco Polo====\n[[File:Vianomarcopolo1.png|thumb|Viano Marco Polo camping edition]]\n\nIn some countries a camping derivative is available - known as the Marco Polo - equipped with a galley (including gas stove, sink, 40 L fridge, and storage), multi-function wardrobe and a sliding bench seat in the rear which can be turned into a large air-sprung bed. A pop-up roof is also standard (electric assist is optional) providing standing height inside. An additional bed can be fitted in the pop-up roof area to increase sleeping capacity to four individuals. Fresh water and waste water tanks are accessible from outside the vehicle, while the gas-cylinder bay is hidden inside an interior cupboard. An auxiliary battery is included under the front passenger seat. Up to six optional individual seats can be fitted for maximum MPV flexibility, but only four seats (including the two-seater bench mentioned above) can be used when in camping mode.\n\nThe Marco Polo was designed and created in partnership with [[Westfalia]] just like Volkswagen camper vans were until 1999. It was then Daimler AG bought a controlling stake in the conversion company meaning Volkswagen had to continue converting their commercial vehicles into camper vans alone.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}\n\n====Viano X-Clusive (2008\u20132010)====\nThis edition was only available in European markets from 2008 to 2010 with either a petrol or diesel V6 engine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/xclusive.0004.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Viano - Viano X-CLUSIVE |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401211852/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/xclusive.0004.html |archivedate=1 April 2010 }}</ref> It was available in either Brilliant Silver or Obsidian Black metallic paint, and featured a redesigned radiator grille, 18-inch alloy wheels, a chromed exhaust tailpipe, side skirts, and unique front and rear bumpers. The interior had pebble or anthracite coloured 'Twin' leather seats and a choice of grey or brown burr walnut wood accents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/xclusive.0003.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Viano - Viano X-CLUSIVE |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100623060346/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/xclusive.0003.html |archivedate=23 June 2010 }}</ref>\n\n====Engines====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!Years!! Model & Transmission !!Engine !!Power !!Torque !!Top Speed !!0-62&nbsp;mph (0-100 km/h) !!Economy !!Emissions\n|-\n!colspan=9|Diesel\n|-\n|2004\u20132007||'''Viano 2.0 CDI'''||2.2 L, 4 in-L||{{convert|109|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|290|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|99|mph|abbr=on}}||17.6 s||{{convert|31.7|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||235 g/km\n|-\n|2004\u20132007||'''Viano 2.0 CDI TouchShift'''||2.2 L, 4 in-L||{{convert|109|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|290|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|98|mph|abbr=on}}||17.3 s||{{convert|31.7|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||235 g/km\n|-\n|2007\u20132010||'''Viano 2.0 CDI'''||2.2 L, 4 in-L||{{convert|116|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|290|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|99|mph|abbr=on}}||17.6 s||{{convert|34.9|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||215 g/km\n|-\n|2007\u20132010||'''Viano 2.0 CDI TouchShift'''||2.2 L, 4 in-L||{{convert|116|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|290|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|98|mph|abbr=on}}||17.3 s||{{convert|32.8|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||229 g/km\n|-\n|2004\u20132010||'''Viano 2.2 CDI'''||2.2 L, 4 in-L||{{convert|150|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|330|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|112|mph|abbr=on}}||14.9 s||{{convert|34.9|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||215 g/km\n|-\n|2004\u20132010||'''Viano 2.2 CDI TouchShift'''||2.2 L, 4 in-L||{{convert|150|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|330|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|111|mph|abbr=on}}||13.0 s||{{convert|32.8|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||229 g/km\n|-\n|2006\u20132010||'''Viano 3.0 CDI TouchShift'''||3.0 L, 6 in-V||{{convert|204|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|440|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|123|mph|abbr=on}}||9.2 s||{{convert|30.7|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||244 g/km\n|-\n!colspan=9|Petrol\n|-\n| || '''Viano 3.0 V6 TouchShift'''||3.2 L, 6 in-V||{{convert|190|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}|| || || || ||\n|-\n| || '''Viano 3.2 V6 TouchShift'''||3.2 L, 6 in-V||{{convert|218|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}|| || || || ||\n|-\n|2004\u20132007||'''Viano 3.7 V6 TouchShift'''||3.7 L, 6 in-V||{{convert|231|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|345|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|119|mph|abbr=on}}||11.0 s||{{convert|23.2|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||294 g/km\n|-\n|2007-||'''Viano 3.5 V6 TouchShift'''||3.5 L, 6 in-V||{{convert|258|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|340|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|127|mph|abbr=on}}||9.3 s||{{convert|23.7|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||284 g/km\n|-\n|n/a||'''Viano 4.4 Brabus TouchShift'''||4.3 L, 6 in-V||{{convert|325|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|430|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|143|mph|abbr=on}}||7.2 s||n/a||n/a\n|-\n|n/a||'''Viano 6.1 Brabus TouchShift'''||6.0 L, 8 in-V||{{convert|426|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|621|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|152|mph|abbr=on}}||6.2 s||n/a||n/a\n|}\n\n====Safety====\nTwo head-on airbags and (on higher trim levels) front side airbags are fitted as standard, with front window airbags available as an option. [[Electronic stability control]] (ESP), [[traction control system]] (ASR), [[anti-lock braking system]] (ABS), [[electronic brakeforce distribution]] (EBV) and [[brake assist]] (BAS) are all fitted as standard. If BAS is activated, the hazard lights flash to warn following motorists that the Viano driver is undertaking an emergency braking manoeuvre.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/overview/safety.0008.html |title=Mercedes-Benz UK - Overview - Safety |publisher=.mercedes-benz.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100106000202/http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/639/overview/safety.0008.html |archivedate=6 January 2010 }}</ref>\n\nEach seat is fitted with a three-point seatbelt with belt tensioner and force limiter and an adjustable head restraint.\n\nThe Viano underwent the [[Euro NCAP]] car safety tests in 2008 and achieved the following ratings:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.euroncap.com/tests/mercedes_benz_viano_2008/343.aspx |title=Mercedes Benz Viano &#124; Euro NCAP - For safer cars crash test safety rating |publisher=Euro NCAP |accessdate=4 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Euro NCAP !!Rating\n|-\n|Adult occupant:\n|{{rating|4|5}}\n|-\n|Child occupant:\n|{{rating|3|5}}\n|-\n|Pedestrian:\n|{{rating|1|4}}\n|}\n\nThe [[Australasian New Car Assessment Program]] (ANCAP) also tested the Viano and gave it a score of 32.66 points out of 37.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ancap.com.au/crashTestRecord.aspx?Id=315 |title=Mercedes-Benz safety &#124; Viano crash test |publisher=ANCAP |accessdate=14 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306131612/http://www.ancap.com.au/crashTestRecord.aspx?Id=315 |archivedate=6 March 2012  }}</ref> It is the only van in Australasia to achieve the maximum five-star rating.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!ANCAP !!Rating\n|-\n|Safety:\n|{{rating|5|5}}\n|}\n\n====Environmental impact====\nEcoTest analysed the emissions from the EU4-compliant 2.0 CDI {{convert|116|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} and 2.2 CDI {{convert|150|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} manuals and the EU5-compliant 2.2 CDI {{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} TouchShift; the results are below:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|{{rating|3|5}} (68/100)<ref name=\"EcoTest\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ecotest.eu/ |title=EcoTest |publisher=Ecotest.eu |accessdate=1 February 2011}}</ref>||2006\u20132010||2.0 CDI Manual||116&nbsp;hp||Diesel\n|-\n|{{rating|2|5}} (46/100)<ref name=\"EcoTest\"/>||2004\u20132010||2.2 CDI Manual||150&nbsp;hp||Diesel\n|}\n\n[http://www.nextgreencar.com/ Next Green Car] - an expert environmental organisation that analyses official vehicle emissions data rated the Viano. These Green Ratings (from 0 (cleanest) to 100 (dirtiest)) are listed below:<ref name=\"Whatgreencar.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nextgreencar.com/view-car/9953/Similar/MERCEDES-BENZ-Viano-Diesel-Manual-6-speed |title=MERCEDES-BENZ Viano CO2 Emissions \u2013 MERCEDES-BENZ Green Ratings at Next Green Car |publisher=Whatgreencar.com |date=3 December 2009 |accessdate=20 July 2012}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''68'''||2006\u20132010||3.0 CDI TouchShift||204&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''70'''||2004\u20132010||2.0 CDI TouchShift||116&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:red;\"| '''71'''||2004\u20132010||2.0 CDI Manual||116&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:red;\"| '''71'''||2004\u20132010||2.2 CDI Manual||150&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:red;\"| '''75'''||2007\u20132010||3.5 V6 TouchShift||258&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:red;\"| '''79'''||2004\u20132010||2.2 CDI TouchShift||150&nbsp;hp\n|}\n\n====Reviews====\n[[File:Mercedes Viano rear 20070913.jpg|thumb|right|Rear 3/4 view pre-facelift]]\nThe Mercedes-Benz Viano has received mixed to positive reviews from the motoring press. The van-based design is seen as a blessing by some critics and a failing by others. As of July 2010 reviews for the facelifted Viano are not available.\n* [[The Automobile Association|AA, The]] {{rating|8|10}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theaa.com/allaboutcars/cartestreports/2009036.html |title=Car Reviews: Mercedes-Benz Viano 3.0 CDI X-CLUSIVE - Long |publisher=The AA |accessdate=4 July 2010}}</ref><br>'Image is everything in the world of business and it should come as no surprise that the Viano is the big cheese in the executive travel world.'\n* [[Autocar (magazine)|Autocar]] {{rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autocar.co.uk/SpecsPrices/SpecsAndPricesModel/Mercedes-Benz-Viano/25220/1928/ |title=Prices and Specs Editions |work=Autocar |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081201211715/http://www.autocar.co.uk/SpecsPrices/SpecsAndPricesModel/Mercedes-Benz-Viano/25220/1928/ |archivedate=1 December 2008 }}</ref><br>'Still more van than MPV. Airport transport.'\n* [[Parker's Car Guides|Parker's]] {{rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/mercedes-benz/viano-2004.aspx |title=New Mercedes-Benz Viano Car Review - Parker's |publisher=Parkers.co.uk |accessdate=4 July 2010}}</ref><br>'Pros: Capable of carrying eight in comfort, massive and versatile interior, superb diesels'.<br>'Cons: Sheer size makes it difficult to manoeuvre, can't hide commercial vehicle origins.'\n* [[Royal Automobile Club plc|RAC]] {{rating|7|10|score=7.2/10 stars}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rac.co.uk/car-reviews/New/Mercedes-Benz/Viano/1067/ |title=Mercedes-Benz Viano Review - Car Reviews |publisher=RAC |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723071252/http://www.rac.co.uk/car-reviews/New/Mercedes-Benz/Viano/1067/ |archivedate=23 July 2011 }}</ref><br>'With its rare combination of spacious seating and generous luggage capacity, the Viano is a paragon of practicality...'\n* [[What Car]]? {{rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.whatcar.com/car-reviews/mercedes-benz/viano-mpv/readers-reviews/25220-7 |title=Mercedes-Benz Viano MPV - Readers Reviews - New Car Review - What Car? |publisher=Whatcar.com |date=23 May 2005 |accessdate=4 July 2010}}</ref><br>'For - Comes with a choice of two wheelbases and three body lengths, plus a variety of seating arrangements and plenty of space inside. The sliding rear side doors ease access.'<br>'Against - It's an expensive option, whose van roots show through in some areas. The engines are noisy and it's not easy to use the car's full versatility...'\n* [[Yahoo|Yahoo! Cars]] {{rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.cars.yahoo.com/car-reviews/car-and-driving/mercedes-viano-range-1003829.html |title=Mercedes Viano Range : VIANO IN THE DARK? - Yahoo!! Cars |publisher=Yahoo! |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070216204056/http://uk.cars.yahoo.com/car-reviews/car-and-driving/mercedes-viano-range-1003829.html |archivedate=16 February 2007 }}</ref><br>\"Most MPVs never make that much sense because when full of people there's nowhere for the lugagge to go. No such problem exists with the vast Viano.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buyacar.co.uk/cars/mercedes_benz/mercedes_benz_viano/review_mercedes-benz_viano_range_561.jhtml |title=Review of the new Mercedes-Benz Viano Range |publisher=Buyacar.co.uk |date=6 March 2006 |accessdate=14 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz V-Class interior.jpg|thumb|V-Class interior]]\n====Motorsports====\n2006: The Viano was a support vehicle in the [[Dakar Rally]] for the [[Mercedes-Benz]] Service and Kwikpower team<ref name=\"daimler1\">{{cite web|url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656174-1-1198680-1-0-0-0-0-0-13457-656174-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |title=Mercedes-Benz Viano 4MATIC class winner in women's rallye &#124; Daimler Global Media Site > Mercedes-Benz Vans > Viano |publisher=Media.daimler.com |date=8 April 2009 |accessdate=4 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708223210/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656174-1-1198680-1-0-0-0-0-0-13457-656174-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |archivedate=8 July 2011 }}</ref>\n2009: The Viano claimed victory in the [[Sport utility vehicle|SUV]] category in the 19th [[Rallye Aicha des Gazelles]] with Irishwoman Jeanette James as pilot and Frenchwoman Anne-Marie Ortola as navigator.<ref name=\"daimler1\"/>\n\n====Production====\n\nOn 16 April 2010 the assembly of the Viano W639 began at the [[Fujian Daimler Automotive]] plant in [[Fuzhou|F\u00fazh\u014du]], China. Forty per cent of the components and automotive parts of the Chinese model version are manufactured by local companies. The Chinese model was launched on the Chinese (Hong Kong, PRC and Republic), the South Korean and Southeast Asian market in April 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.daimler.com/dccom/0-5-7153-49-1288633-1-0-0-0-0-0-9293-7145-0-0-0-0-0-0-0.html |title=Erstes Kundenfahrzeug bei Fujian Daimler Automotive produziert |publisher=Daimler AG |date=16 April 2010 |accessdate=17 August 2010 |language=German}}{{dead link|date=March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fujiandaimler.com.cn/ |script-title=zh:\u798f\u5efa\u6234\u59c6\u52d2\u6c7d\u8f66\u5de5\u4e1a\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8 |publisher=Fujian Daimler Automotive |accessdate=17 August 2010 |language=Chinese, English |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140209113518/http://www.fujiandaimler.com.cn/ |archivedate=9 February 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===2010 facelift===\n====Viano====\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz Viano Lang CDI 2.2 BlueEFFICIENCY Trend (V 639, Facelift) \u2013 Frontansicht, 13. Juni 2011, Wuppertal.jpg|thumb|Post-facelift Viano, long version]]\n[[File:2011 Mercedes-Benz Viano (V 639 MY12) Edition 125 CDI 3.0 BlueEFFICIENCY van (2015-07-24) 02.jpg|thumbnail|right|Rear view of Viano, long version]]\n\nChanges to the Viano range include standard BlueEFFICIENCY technology, new interior trim materials, new ambient lighting system with dimmable individual LED reading lamps and fibre optic units, optional rear seat entertainment system, redesigned cockpit, new suspension with front and rear axles revised and specially tuned to match each specific model and EU 5 emission standards compliance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emercedesbenz.com/autos/mercedes-benz/viano/new-mercedes-benz-viano-van-offers-comfort-and-efficiency/ |title=New Mercedes-Benz Viano Van Offers Comfort and Efficiency |publisher=eMercedesBenz |accessdate=4 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe face lifted range included four and six-cylinder diesel and petrol engines rated at {{convert|100|kW|hp PS|0|abbr=on}} to {{convert|190|kW|hp PS|0|abbr=on}} (CDI 2.0, CDI 2.2, CDI 3.0, 3.5).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1309639-1-0-0-0-0-1-11701-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |title=Comfort, Sustainability, Design, Driving Pleasure: The new generation of Mercedes-Benz Viano |access-date=4 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131206185456/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1309639-1-0-0-0-0-1-11701-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |archive-date=6 December 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1325908-1-0-0-0-0-1-11702-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1386063037869 |title=Engine and drive system: clean, extremely economical and offering top-notch performance |access-date=4 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131206183920/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1325908-1-0-0-0-0-1-11702-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1386063037869 |archive-date=6 December 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nA four-wheel drive (4MATIC) is optional on models with 4-cylinder diesel engines. In normal operation the system transfers driving power in a 35:65 split between the front and rear axles. The 4MATIC system does not have mechanical differential locks, but an electronic traction system (4ETS). If one or more wheels loses traction on a slippery surface, the system applies brief pulses of brake pressure to the spinning wheels thus increasing torque to wheels with good grip. Vehicles with four-wheel drive have a higher ride height, which increases approach, departure and breakover angles (20\u00b0/28\u00b0/19\u00b0 respectively, versus 14\u00b0/22\u00b0/14\u00b0 in conventional rear-wheel-drive models). The all-wheel drive adds {{convert|80|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} to the total weight of the vehicle.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1385243-1-0-0-0-0-0-11702-0-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |title=Mercedes-Benz Viano 4MATIC: traction, comfort and safety in perfection |publisher=media.daimler.com |accessdate=6 August 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326024757/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1385243-1-0-0-0-0-0-11702-0-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |archive-date=26 March 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n====Vito====\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz Vito Kombi Extralang 116 CDI BlueEFFICIENCY (V 639) \u2013 Frontansicht, 3. Juli 2011, Essen.jpg|thumb|right|Post-facelift Vito]]\nThe facelifted version of the Vito began from September 2010, and features restyled front and rear lights, restyled front bumpers, and more-efficient diesel engines adapted from the [[Mercedes-Benz Sprinter]] range. The Vito's suspension, instrumentation, steering wheel, and overall quality of materials was also improved.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emercedesbenz.com/autos/mercedes-benz/vito/mercedes-benz-vito-new-generation-sets-new-benchmarks-in-vans-segment/ |title=Mercedes-Benz Vito New-Generation Sets New Benchmarks in Vans Segment |publisher=Mercedes-Benz |date=2 July 2010 |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nEarly models included Vito 110 CDI, Vito 113 CDI, Vito 116 CDI, Vito 122 CDI, Vito 126, with 3 body lengths (compact, long, extra-long).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656637-1-1325913-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408492413801 |title=Summary: The new Mercedes-Benz Vito |access-date=19 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821025438/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656637-1-1325913-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408492413801 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656637-1-1325966-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408494583672 |title=Exterior and body: new highlights underscore the Vito's robust appearance |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821014919/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656637-1-1325966-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408494583672 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n====Vito E-CELL (2010\u2013)====\n[[File:Vito E-Cell.jpg|thumb|right|Presentation of the 'Mercedes-Benz Vito E-Cell' at the headquarters of the [[European Committee of the Regions]], during ''Open Days'' ([[Brussels]], 5 October 2010)]]\n\nThe E-Cell was unveiled in 2010 Post Expo,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1317008-1-1428232-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408494810307 |title=Mercedes-Benz showcases the Vito E-CELL at the Post Expo in Stuttgart |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821004421/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1317008-1-1428232-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408494810307 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> powered by a 36 kWh lithium-ion battery located in the underfloor unit, electric motor rated {{convert|81|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|280|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} of torque.\n\nIn 2012 a seven-seater Vito E-Cell was unveiled at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2012|2012 Geneva Motor Show]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-614307-1-1466038-1-0-0-1466283-0-1-12759-614216-0-0-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1386960513874 |title=Mercedes-Benz at the 2012 Geneva Motor Show: Two world premieres and three European premieres in Geneva - Two world premieres and three European premieres in Geneva: Dynamism and efficiency |access-date=13 December 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213195733/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-614307-1-1466038-1-0-0-1466283-0-1-12759-614216-0-0-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1386960513874 |archive-date=13 December 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> with electric motor ({{convert|60|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}}, {{convert|280|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}), power electronics, transformer and AC/DC charger under the bonnet; lithium-ion batteries under the passenger compartment floor.\n\nThe Vito E-Cell is the first [[electric vehicle]] mass-produced in Spain. It will be fabricated by [[Mercedes-Benz]] Spain, in the factory of [[Vitoria-Gasteiz]]. The first manufactured units (91 already) were presented on 7 February 2011. The goal is to produce 474 units by the end of the year. Most of them will be sold to foreign companies (mainly in Germany; [[Berlin]] and [[Stuttgart]]), though the [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque]] supermarket gamble [[Eroski]] has got four vans for distribution duties. Last year, the government made a plan in order to encourage this kind of cars. 590 million \u20ac will be funded, from which 7 have gone to the 'E-Cell' project. This project will also be supported by the Basque and German governments.\n\nMercedes-Benz has chosen its Spanish factory in Vitoria for fabricating exclusively this van, which will substitute the current models Vito and Viano (the commercial-transport and passenger-carrier versions, respectively). Mercedes-Benz expected 100 vehicles to be produced by the end of 2010 and a further 2,000 by the end of 2011.<ref>{{cite web |last=Abuelsamid |first=Sam |url=http://green.autoblog.com/2010/07/30/mercedes-benz-introduces-new-vito-e-cell-van/ |title=Mercedes-Benz introduces new Vito E-Cell van \u2013 Autoblog Green |publisher=Green.autoblog.com |date=30 July 2010 |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe Vito E-Cell utilizes a front-wheel drive setup to save installation space for a 36-[[kWh]] [[lithium-ion battery]] pack housed underneath the van's cargo area. The E-Cell's [[electric motor]] has {{convert|60|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|280|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} of torque. The electric van has a range of {{convert|81|mi||0|abbr=on}} and a top speed of {{convert|50|mph||0|abbr=on}}.\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://green.autoblog.com/2011/05/04/europcar-to-offer-mercedes-benz-vito-e-cell-electric-van-rentals/ |title=Europcar to offer Mercedes-Benz Vito E-Cell electric van rentals |author=Eric Loveday |publisher=AutoblogGreen |date=4 May 2011 |accessdate=10 June 2011}}</ref> The UK market was allocated 50 vehicles for the first year. All customers are to be vetted to ensure suitability and must return the van after four years to Mercedes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vanlocator.co.uk/van-sales/2011/07/01/mercedes-benz-vito-e-cell-hits-the-uk// |title=Mercedes-Benz Vito E-Cell Hits the UK |author=Van Locator |publisher=Focus Publishing |date=1 July 2011 |accessdate=10 July 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe Vito E-Cell is a long van, with a distance of 3.2 meters between the axes, so that there is enough space for the batteries. With this aim of saving space, only the front-drive version is offered, unlike in the previous model, so a long development was needed, although some suspension components of the AWD ([[all-wheel drive]]) version were used. The vehicle has a payload capacity of {{convert|900|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}, and a permissible total weight of three tons (3.050&nbsp;kg, exactly). <br />\nThe car does not show external changes with the other versions (except for the decoration): the body has not been modified, both the double side door and the helpful back 'gate' remain as before. The place for the refueling has also been used for the recharging connection.\n\nThe Vito E-Cell has got a complete and modern equipment. Among the main novelties, this model has a special [[heater]] connected to the high voltage network and to the basic heating system, in order to ensure pleasant conditions even in the coldest months.\n\nIn terms of safety, the new Mercedes keeps the same level as the other Vito models. The vehicle has an [[internal combustion engine]], so, if a collision occurs, the batteries are protected by a shock element. The active safety also makes that the high-technology voltage network turns off when the airbag control unit activates. The Vito E-Cell comes standard with the [[Electronic stability control|Electronic Stability Program]] (ESP) and dual [[airbag]]s.\n\nThis van is driven by an [[electric battery]]. This battery is placed under the chassis (where the [[petrol tank]] and the [[prop-shaft]] are normally), while the engine, the transformer and the charger are located in the engine's (a block of four or six cylinders) usual position, under the hood.\n\nThe battery consists of a [[Lithium ion battery]] pack split into 16 modules with 192 cells in all, with high energy density and a rated voltage of 360 volts. They are supplied by the company [[Magna International|Magna]], and they have a maximum range of {{convert|130|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} (just as the engine), but this can be reduced by the weather conditions, the ground's topography or even the cargo volume.  It is considered that a range between 90&nbsp;km and 100&nbsp;km could be more realistic.  Either way, it is supposed to be enough for a workday in urban delivery. The batteries weigh {{convert|550|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}; their life is unknown. Their total charge time is six hours through a high voltage system (380 or 400 volts); with a domestic 230 volt supply the total charge time is double, about 12 hours. The total battery capacity is 36&nbsp;kWh, 32&nbsp;kWh are available for the vehicle operation. Moreover, Mercedes-Benz offers the vehicle in the form of 'renting', in which the manufacturer takes charge of updating the batteries when necessary.\n\nThe electric engine is a permanent synchronous magnet drive with a constant power of {{convert|60|kW|hp PS|0|abbr=on}} and a maximum power of {{convert|70|kW|hp PS|0|abbr=on}}. The top speed is limited to {{convert|80|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}, and it has a maximum [[torque]] of {{convert|280|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} instantly available, which lets the van have a similar dynamic performance to one equipped with a modern diesel engine.\n\n====Engines====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Petrol engines<ref name=EandD>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656637-1-1325917-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408494289853 |title=Engine and drive system: unmatched economy and environmental friendliness |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820234013/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656637-1-1325917-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408494289853 |archive-date=20 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"D1549054\">{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1325908-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408495651355 |title=Engine and drive system: clean, extremely economical and offering top-notch performance |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821005112/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656624-1-1325908-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408495651355 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n!Model!!Years!!Type/code!!Power, torque/rpm\n|-\n|Viano 3.0||2010-||{{convert|3199|cc|abbr=on}} V6 ([[Mercedes-Benz M112 engine|M 112 E 32]])|| {{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 5600, {{convert|270|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 2750-4750\n|-\n|Viano 3.5||2010-||{{convert|3498|cc|abbr=on}} V6 ([[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine|M 272 KE 35]])|| {{convert|258|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 5900, {{convert|340|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 2500-5000\n|-\n|Vito 119||2010-||{{convert|3199|cc|abbr=on}} V6 ([[Mercedes-Benz M112 engine|M 112 E 32]])|| {{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 5600, {{convert|270|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 2750-4750\n|-\n|Vito 126||2010-||{{convert|3498|cc|abbr=on}} V6 ([[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine|M 272 KE 35]])|| {{convert|258|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 5900, {{convert|340|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 2500-4000\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Diesel engines<ref name=EandD/><ref name=\"D1549054\"/>\n!Model!!Years!!Type/code!!Power, torque/rpm\n|-\n|Viano 2.0 CDI||2010-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}