ICIENCY||2010-||ECO Gear six-speed manual, five-speed automatic\n|-\n|Viano 2.2 CDI 4MATIC||2010-||five-speed automatic\n|-\n|Viano 2.2 CDI BlueEFFICIENCY 4MATIC||2010-||five-speed automatic\n|-\n|Viano 3.0 CDI||2010-||five-speed automatic\n|-\n|Viano 3.0 CDI BlueEFFICIENCY||2010-||five-speed automatic\n|-\n|}\n\n====Performance====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Diesel engines\n!Model!!Years!!top speed!!acceleration (s)!!fuel economy!!emission (g/km)\n|-\n|Viano 2.0 CDI||2010-||{{convert|108|mph|abbr=on}}||14.1||{{convert|38.7|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||192\n|-\n|Viano 2.0 CDI TouchShift||2010-||{{convert|107|mph|abbr=on}}||13.1||{{convert|34.5|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||216\n|-\n|Viano 2.2 CDI||2010-||{{convert|117|mph|abbr=on}}||12.1||{{convert|38.7|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||192\n|-\n|Viano 2.2 CDI TouchShift||2010-||{{convert|113|mph|abbr=on}}||11.1||{{convert|34.5|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||216\n|-\n|Viano 3.0 CDI TouchShift||2010-||{{convert|125|mph|abbr=on}}||9.1||{{convert|32.8|mpgimp|l/100 km|abbr=on}}||226\n|-\n|}\n\nAll Viano and Vito engines conformed to [[European emission standards|Euro 5]] emission standards.\n\n====Security====\nThe Viano was tested by Thatcham's New Vehicle Security Ratings (NVSR) organisation and achieved the following ratings:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thatcham.org/nvsr/index.jsp?page=202&s=car |title=New Vehicle Security Ratings |publisher=Thatcham.org |accessdate=14 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110802043903/http://www.thatcham.org/nvsr/index.jsp?page=202&s=car |archivedate=2 August 2011  }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!NVSR !!Rating\n|-\n|Theft of car:\n|{{rating|5|5}}\n|-\n|Theft from car:\n|{{rating|3|5}}\n|}\n\n====Environmental impact====\nEcoTest analysed the emissions from the EU4-compliant 2.0 CDI {{convert|116|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} and 2.2 CDI {{convert|150|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} manuals and the EU5-compliant 2.2 CDI {{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} TouchShift; the results are below:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|{{rating|3|5}} (64/100)<ref name=\"EcoTest\"/>||2010 - on||2.2 CDI TouchShift||163&nbsp;hp||Diesel\n|}\n\n[http://www.nextgreencar.com/ Next Green Car] - an expert environmental organisation that analyses official vehicle emissions data rated the Viano. These Green Ratings (from 0 (cleanest) to 100 (dirtiest)) are listed below:<ref name=\"Whatgreencar.com\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''53'''||2010-on||2.0 CDI Manual||136&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''53'''||2010-on||2.2 CDI Manual||163&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''59'''||2010-on||2.0 CDI TouchShift||136&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''59'''||2010-on||2.2 CDI TouchShift||163&nbsp;hp\n|-\n| style=\"background:orange;\"| '''62'''||2010-on||3.0 CDI TouchShift||224&nbsp;hp\n|}\n\n===2013 update===\nDuring 2013 a number of special editions were launched; including the Grand Edition Viano launched at the [[Geneva Motor Show]]. Two special version for the Japanese markets were launched the V350 White Edition (50 units) and Black Edition (170 units) with additional equipment, large alloy wheels and leather interior.<ref>[http://www.mercedes-benz.jp/news/release/2013/20130606_1.pdf V\u30af\u30e9\u30b9\u7279\u5225\u4ed5\u69d8\u8eca2\u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u3092\u9650\u5b9a\u767a\u58f2]</ref>\n\nTwo updated camper vans were launched at the 2013 Caravan Salon; the Fun and Marco Polo.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1580131-1-1626219-1-0-0-0-0-1-11701-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |title=Mercedes-Benz at the Caravan Salon 2013 - Reaching for the stars: Mercedes-Benz Commercial Vehicles with a broad portfolio at the Caravan Salon 2013 |access-date=4 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221123012/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1580131-1-1626219-1-0-0-0-0-1-11701-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |archive-date=21 February 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n====Engines====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Petrol engines\n!Model!!Years!!Type/code!!Power, torque/rpm\n|-\n|Viano 3.0||2013-||{{convert|3199|cc|abbr=on}} V6 ([[Mercedes-Benz M112 engine|M 112 E 32]])|| {{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 5600, {{convert|270|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 2750-4750\n|-\n|Viano 3.5||2013-||{{convert|3498|cc|abbr=on}} V6 ([[Mercedes-Benz M272 engine|M 272 KE 35]])|| {{convert|258|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 5900, {{convert|340|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 2500-5000\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Diesel engines\n!Model!!Years!!Type/code!!Power, torque/rpm\n|-\n|Viano 2.2 CDI||2013-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|360|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1600-2400\n|-\n|Viano 3.0 CDI||2013-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} V6 turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM642 engine|OM 642 DE 30 LA]])|| {{convert|224|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|440|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2800\n|}\n\nUK models included only 2.2 CDI (long/extra long), 3.0 CDI (long/extra long).\n\n====Transmissions====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Petrol engines\n!Model!!Years!!Types\n|-\n|Viano 3.0||2013-||?\n|-\n|Viano 3.5||2013-||?\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Diesel engines\n!Model!!Years!!Types\n|-\n|Viano 2.2 CDI||2013-||6-speed manual, 5-speed automatic\n|-\n|Viano 3.0 CDI||2013-||6-speed manual, 5-speed automatic\n|}\n\n====Production====\nAs of 14 November 2013, Daimler's van joint venture Fujian Benz Automotive Co. (FBAC) has secured an order by the Dalian Wanda Group comprising 85 Mercedes-Benz Viano 3.0L vans.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656505-1-1649560-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408498730211 |title=Major Chinese order with an element of glamor: Dalian Wanda Group orders 85 Mercedes-Benz Viano vans |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821033650/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656505-1-1649560-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408498730211 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Third generation (W447; 2014\u2013present)==\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = W447\n| image = Mercedes-Benz V 250 BlueTEC Edition 1 Lang (V 447) \u2013 Frontansicht, 18. Oktober 2015, Ratingen.jpg\n| aka = Mercedes-Benz Viano<br />Mercedes-Benz Valente (Australia)<br />Mercedes-Benz V-Class<br />Mercedes-Benz Metris (Canada and United States)<br />Mercedes-Benz EQV (Electric Concept)\n| assembly = {{ubl |Spain: [[Vitoria, Spain|Vitoria-Gasteiz]] (Mercedes-Benz Espana, S.A.) |Spain: [[Alcobendas]] ([[Complete knock down|CKD]]) |Mexico: [[Santiago Tianguistenco]] |Argentina: [[Buenos Aires]] |China: [[Fuzhou|F\u00fazh\u014du]] ([[Fujian Daimler Automotive|Fujian Daimler]]) |India: [[Pune]] ([[Mercedes-Benz India]])}}\n| production = 2014\u2013present\n| body_style = 4-door [[van]]<br/>4-door [[minibus]]\n| engine = 1.6L [[Mercedes-Benz OM622 engine|OM 622 DE 16 LA]] I4 Turbo Diesel<br>1.7L [[Mercedes-Benz OM622 engine|OM 622 DE 17 LA]] I4 Turbo Diesel<br>2.0L [[Mercedes-Benz OM654 engine#OM_654q|OM 654]] I4 two-stage turbo Diesel<br>2.2L [[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA red.]] I4 two-stage turbo Diesel<br>2.0L M274 I4 Petrol (China, USA&Canada)\n| motor = 2x asynchronous [[electric motor]]s (Mercedes-Benz EQV)<br>Permanent synchronous magnet electric motor (eVito Tourer)\n| transmission = ECO Gear 6-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]<br>[[7G-TRONIC|7G-TRONIC PLUS]] 7-speed [[Automatic transmission|Automatic]]<br>9-speed ''[[9G-Tronic]]'' [[automatic transmission|automatic]]<br>Single speed with fixed ratio (Mercedes-Benz EQV / eVito Tourer)\n| layout = [[Front-engine, front-wheel-drive layout|FF Layout]]<br>[[Front engine, rear-wheel-drive layout|FR Layout]]<br>[[Front-engine, four-wheel-drive layout|F4 Layout]]\n| wheelbase = {{convert|3200|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (SWB) <br> {{convert|3430|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (LWB)\n| length = {{convert|5140|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (SWB) <br> {{convert|5370|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (LWB)\n| width = {{convert|1928|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (body only) <br> {{convert|2057|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (mirrors folded) <br> {{convert|2249|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (mirrors unfolded)\n| height = {{convert|1901|-|1908|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight =\n| engines =\n}}\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz V 250 BlueTEC Edition 1 Lang (V 447) \u2013 Heckansicht, 18. Oktober 2015, Ratingen.jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-Benz V-Class (W447)]]\n[[File:2017 Mercedes-Benz Metris Cargo Van 2.0L front.jpg|thumb|left|2017 Mercedes-Benz Metris]]\n\nThe third generation V-Class was launched in 2014 as a full size MPV to replace the Viano and [[Mercedes-Benz R-Class|R-Class]].<ref>[http://www.worldcarfans.com/113102164746/2014-mercedes-benz-v-class-interior-officially-revealed 2014 Mercedes-Benz V-Class interior officially revealed]</ref> However, it was marketed as a successor to the Mercedes-Benz Viano.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1641994-1-0-0-0-0-1-11702-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |title=Mercedes-Benz TecDay : The new V-Class - The Mercedes among Full Size MPVs |access-date=4 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131206185441/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1641994-1-0-0-0-0-1-11702-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html |archive-date=6 December 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Sales commenced in Germany in May 2014, with European sales following in June.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1666696-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1391382309278 |title=The model range: Versatile and individual for the most widely ranging requirements |access-date=4 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219141935/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1666696-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1391382309278 |archive-date=19 February 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The car is sold in the United States and Canada as the '''Mercedes-Benz Metris''' since 2015 as a 2016 model year. At the time of its introduction it was the least expensive starting price for a new Mercedes-Benz model in the United States according to ''Car and Driver'' magazine.<ref name=\"caranddriver.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.caranddriver.com/mercedes-benz/metris|title=Mercedes-Benz Metris - Car and Driver|work=caranddriver.com|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe V-Class was a long-wheelbase model initially, with compact and extra-long variants due at a later date.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1666677-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1391362219270 |title=The new V-Class: The Mercedes among MPVs |access-date=4 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219134925/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1666677-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1391362219270 |archive-date=19 February 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>[http://www.autoblog.com/2014/01/30/2014-mercedes-v-class-van/ Mercedes debuts new V-Class van]</ref> A special launch model based on the V 250 BlueTEC is called Edition 1, and is fitted with a range of additional equipment including leather interior, Burmeister sound system and large alloy wheels and Agility Control suspension system.\n{{clear left}}\n===Vito (2014\u2013present)===\n[[File:2017 Mercedes-Benz Vito 111 CDi 1.6.jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-Benz Vito (W447)]]\n[[File:2015 Mercedes-Benz Vito 116 Bluetec 2.1 Rear.jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-Benz Vito (W447)]]\nChanges to Vito included standard [[Attention Assist]] and [[Crosswind stabilization|Crosswind Assist]], optional [[Intelligent Light System]] (LED indicators, LED daytime running lamps, LED low-beam headlamps, main beam with [[cornering light]] function).\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled in 2014 International Commercial Vehicles show.<ref>[http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1580131-1-1727270-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html Mercedes-Benz Vans at the 2014 International Commercial Vehicles show (IAA): Public premiere for the Vito, flanked by the Sprinter and Citan \u2013 Mercedes-Benz Vans at the 2014 International Commercial Vehicles show (IAA)]</ref>\n{{clear left}}\n\n===Production===\nProduction of V-Class in Vitoria, Spain plant began in March 2014, followed by Mercedes-Benz Vito in autumn 2014.<ref>[http://www.daimler.com/dccom/0-5-7153-1-1712380-1-0-0-0-0-0-9293-0-0-0-0-0-0-0-0.html Europcar adds 175 new Mercedes-Benz V-Class MPVs to its rental car fleet] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821032441/http://www.daimler.com/dccom/0-5-7153-1-1712380-1-0-0-0-0-0-9293-0-0-0-0-0-0-0-0.html |date=21 August 2014 }}</ref> Also, it started production in Argentina<ref>http://autoblog.com.ar/2012/10/05/mercedes-benz-fabricara-la-nueva-vito-en-la-argentina/</ref> and production at the [[Fujian Daimler Automotive|Fujian Daimler]] plant in [[Fuzhou|F\u00fazh\u014du]], China started in March 2016.\n\n[[File:Mercedes V-Class (13146569465).jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-Benz V-Class interior]]\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz EQV at IAA 2019 IMG 0406.jpg|thumb|Mercedes-Benz EQV]]\n{{clear}}\n\n=== Engines<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1666754-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408496732448 |title=Drive system - Efficient driving pleasure: six-cylinder power with four-cylinder fuel consumption |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821025435/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1642573-1-1666754-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408496732448 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1722750-1-1722788-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408497143489 |title=One for all: choice of front, rear or all-wheel drive |access-date=20 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821041648/http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1722750-1-1722788-1-0-0-0-0-1-0-1549054-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html?TS=1408497143489 |archive-date=21 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\"\n|+Diesel engines\n!Model!!Years!!Type/code!!Power, torque/rpm\n|-\n|V 200 CDI||2014-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA red.]])|| {{convert|136|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|330|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1200-2400\n|-\n|V 220 CDI||2014-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|380|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|V 250 BlueTEC||2014-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|440|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400<br>overboost: {{convert|200|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|480|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|Vito 109 CDI||2014-||{{convert|1598|cc|abbr=on}} I4 turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM622 engine|OM 622 DE 16 LA]])|| {{convert|88|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|230|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1500-2000\n|-\n|Vito 110 CDI||2020-||{{convert|1698|cc|abbr=on}} I4 turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM622 engine|OM 622 DE 17 LA]])|| {{convert|114|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|270|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1500-2000\n|-\n|Vito 111 CDI||2014-||{{convert|1598|cc|abbr=on}} I4 turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM622 engine|OM 622 DE 16 LA]])|| {{convert|114|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|270|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1500-2500\n|-\n|Vito 114 CDI||2014-2020||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA red.]])|| {{convert|136|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|330|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1200-2400\n|-\n|Vito 114 CDI||2020-||{{convert|1698|cc|abbr=on}} I4 turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM622 engine|OM 622 DE 17 LA]])|| {{convert|136|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|330|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1200-2400\n|-\n|Vito 116 CDI||2014-2020||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|380|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|Vito 116 CDI||2020-||{{convert|1950|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|380|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|Vito 119 BlueTEC||2014-||{{convert|2143|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|440|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|Vito 119 CDI BlueTEC||2020-||{{convert|1950|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM651 engine|OM 651 DE 22 LA]])|| {{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|440|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|Vito 124 CDI||2020-||{{convert|1950|cc|abbr=on}} I4 two-stage turbo ([[Mercedes-Benz OM654 engine|OM 654q]])|| {{convert|239|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 3800, {{convert|500|Nm|0|abbr=on}} at 1400-2400\n|-\n|eVito Tourer||2021-||Permanent synchronous magnet electric motor|| {{convert|204|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}}, {{convert|362|Nm|0|abbr=on}}\n|}\n\nBlueEFFICIENCY package is standard on all versions of V-Class featuring the 7G-TRONIC PLUS automatic transmission and is optionally available for all variants with 6-speed manual transmission.\n\nBlue Efficiency package is available for Vito with OM 651 engine and rear-wheel drive, and standard for all Vito models with automatic transmission and a car registration.\n\nOverboost is available for vehicles with 7G-TRONIC PLUS transmission and AGILITY SELECT, with transmission mode set to \"Comfort\" (C), \"Sport\" (S), or \"Manual\" (M).\n\n===Transmissions===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\"\n|+Diesel engines\n!Model!!Years!!Types\n|-\n|V 200 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS with DIRECT SELECT lever and DIRECT SELECT shift paddles)\n|-\n|V 220 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS with DIRECT SELECT lever and DIRECT SELECT shift paddles)\n|-\n|V 250 BlueTEC||2014-||7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS with DIRECT SELECT lever and DIRECT SELECT shift paddles)\n|-\n|Vito 109 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual\n|-\n|Vito 110 CDI||2020-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual\n|-\n|Vito 111 CDI||2014-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual\n|-\n|Vito 114 CDI||2014-2020||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS)\n|-\n|Vito 114 CDI||2020-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 9-speed ''[[9G-Tronic]]'' [[automatic transmission|automatic]]\n|-\n|Vito 116 CDI||2014-2020||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS)\n|-\n|Vito 116 CDI||2020-||ECO Gear 6-speed manual, 9-speed automatic (9G-Tronic)\n|-\n|Vito 119 BlueTEC||2014-||7-speed automatic (7G-TRONIC PLUS)\n|-\n||Vito 119 CDI||2020-||9-speed automatic (9G-Tronic)\n|-\n||Vito 124 CDI||2020-||9-speed automatic (9G-Tronic)\n|-\n|eVito Tourer||2021-||Single speed with fixed ratio\n|}\n\nV-Class with 7G-TRONIC PLUS transmission includes optional AGILITY SELECT system with 4 transmission modes (\"ECO\" (E), \"Comfort\" (C), \"Sport\" (S) and \"Manual\" (M)).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www5.mercedes-benz.com/en/vehicles/passenger-cars/v-class/ Mercedes-Benz V-Class]\n* [http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/new_cars/models/viano/_639.flash.html?csref=mbuk_viano_url_061211 Mercedes-Benz Viano (UK)]\n* [http://www2.mercedes-benz.co.uk/content/unitedkingdom/mpc/mpc_unitedkingdom_website/en/home_mpc/van/home/new_vans/the-new-vito.html Mercedes-Benz Vito (UK)]\n*[http://www.mbvans.com/sprinter/commercial-vans/metris-cargo-van MB Vans - Metris Cargo Van]\n\n{{Mercedes-Benz timeline 1990\u20132019}}\n{{Mercedes-Benz timeline 2020 to date}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[Category:M